   1# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   2# Purpose:       notation is a set of annotated music21 notation wrappers for use
   3#                by musicdiff.
   4#                musicdiff is a package for comparing music scores using music21.
   5#
   6# Authors:       Greg Chapman <gregc@mac.com>
   7#                musicdiff is derived from:
   8#                   https://github.com/fosfrancesco/music-score-diff.git
   9#                   by Francesco Foscarin <foscarin.francesco@gmail.com>
  10#
  11# Copyright:     (c) 2022-2024 Francesco Foscarin, Greg Chapman
  12# License:       MIT, see LICENSE
  13# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  14
  15__docformat__ = "google"
  16
  17import html
  18from fractions import Fraction
  19import typing as t
  20
  21import music21 as m21
  22from music21.common import OffsetQL, opFrac
  23
  24from musicdiff import M21Utils
  25from musicdiff import DetailLevel
  26
  27class AnnNote:
  28    def __init__(
  29        self,
  30        general_note: m21.note.GeneralNote,
  31        gap_dur: OffsetQL,
  32        enhanced_beam_list: list[str],
  33        tuplet_list: list[str],
  34        tuplet_info: list[str],
  35        parent_chord: m21.chord.ChordBase | None = None,
  36        chord_offset: OffsetQL | None = None,  # only set if this note is inside a chord
  37        detail: DetailLevel | int = DetailLevel.Default,
  38    ) -> None:
  39        """
  40        Extend music21 GeneralNote with some precomputed, easily compared information about it.
  41
  42        Args:
  43            general_note (music21.note.GeneralNote): The music21 note/chord/rest to extend.
  44            gap_dur (OffsetQL): gap since end of last note (or since start of measure, if
  45                first note in measure).  Usually zero.
  46            enhanced_beam_list (list): A list of beaming information about this GeneralNote.
  47            tuplet_list (list): A list of basic tuplet info about this GeneralNote.
  48            tuplet_info (list): A list of detailed tuplet info about this GeneralNote.
  49            detail (DetailLevel | int): What level of detail to use during the diff.
  50                Can be DecoratedNotesAndRests, OtherObjects, AllObjects, Default (currently
  51                AllObjects), or any combination (with | or &~) of those or NotesAndRests,
  52                Beams, Tremolos, Ornaments, Articulations, Ties, Slurs, Signatures,
  53                Directions, Barlines, StaffDetails, ChordSymbols, Ottavas, Arpeggios, Lyrics,
  54                Style, Metadata, or Voicing.
  55        """
  56        self.general_note: int | str = general_note.id
  57        self.is_in_chord: bool = False
  58        self.note_idx_in_chord: int | None = None
  59        if parent_chord is not None:
  60            # This is what visualization uses to color the note red (chord id and note idx)
  61            self.general_note = parent_chord.id
  62            self.is_in_chord = True
  63            self.note_idx_in_chord = parent_chord.notes.index(general_note)
  64
  65        # A lot of stuff is carried by the parent_chord (if present) or the
  66        # general_note (if parent_chord not present); we call that the carrier
  67        carrier: m21.note.GeneralNote = parent_chord or general_note
  68
  69        self.gap_dur: OffsetQL = gap_dur
  70        self.beamings: list[str] = enhanced_beam_list
  71        self.tuplets: list[str] = tuplet_list
  72        self.tuplet_info: list[str] = tuplet_info
  73
  74        self.note_offset: OffsetQL = 0.
  75        self.note_dur_type: str = ''
  76        self.note_dur_dots: int = 0
  77        self.note_is_grace: bool = False
  78
  79        # fullNameSuffix is only for text output, it is not involved in comparison at all.
  80        # It is of the form "Dotted Quarter Rest", etc.
  81        self.fullNameSuffix: str = general_note.duration.fullName
  82        if isinstance(general_note, m21.note.Rest):
  83            self.fullNameSuffix += " Rest"
  84        elif isinstance(general_note, m21.chord.ChordBase):
  85            if parent_chord is None:
  86                self.fullNameSuffix += " Chord"
  87            else:
  88                # we're actually annotating one of the notes in the chord
  89                self.fullNameSuffix += " Note"
  90        elif isinstance(general_note, (m21.note.Note, m21.note.Unpitched)):
  91            self.fullNameSuffix += " Note"
  92        else:
  93            self.fullNameSuffix += " Note"
  94        self.fullNameSuffix = self.fullNameSuffix.lower()
  95
  96        if not DetailLevel.includesVoicing(detail):
  97            # if we're comparing the individual notes, we need to make a note of
  98            # offset and visual duration to be used later when searching for matching
  99            # notes in the measures being compared.
 100
 101            # offset
 102            if chord_offset is None:
 103                self.note_offset = general_note.offset
 104            else:
 105                self.note_offset = chord_offset
 106
 107            # visual duration and graceness
 108            self.note_dur_type = carrier.duration.type
 109            self.note_dur_dots = carrier.duration.dots
 110            self.note_is_grace = carrier.duration.isGrace
 111
 112        self.styledict: dict = {}
 113
 114        if DetailLevel.includesStyle(detail):
 115            # we will take style from the individual note, and then override with
 116            # style from the chord (following music21's MusicXML exporter).
 117            if M21Utils.has_style(general_note):
 118                self.styledict = M21Utils.obj_to_styledict(general_note, detail)
 119
 120            if parent_chord is not None:
 121                if M21Utils.has_style(parent_chord):
 122                    parentstyledict = M21Utils.obj_to_styledict(parent_chord, detail)
 123                    for k, v in parentstyledict.items():
 124                        self.styledict[k] = v
 125
 126        self.noteshape: str = 'normal'
 127        self.noteheadFill: bool | None = None
 128        self.noteheadParenthesis: bool = False
 129        self.stemDirection: str = 'unspecified'
 130        if DetailLevel.includesStyle(detail) and isinstance(general_note, m21.note.NotRest):
 131            if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 132                # because general_note is NotRest, parent_chord must also be (might be
 133                # a chord instead of a note, but that still works)
 134                assert isinstance(carrier, m21.note.NotRest)
 135            self.stemDirection = carrier.stemDirection
 136
 137            if parent_chord is None:
 138                self.noteshape = general_note.notehead
 139                self.noteheadFill = general_note.noteheadFill
 140                self.noteheadParenthesis = general_note.noteheadParenthesis
 141            else:
 142                # try general_note first, but if nothing about note head is specified,
 143                # go with whatever parent_chord says.
 144                if (general_note.notehead != 'normal'
 145                        or general_note.noteheadParenthesis
 146                        or general_note.noteheadFill is not None):
 147                    self.noteheadParenthesis = general_note.noteheadParenthesis
 148                    self.noteshape = general_note.notehead
 149                    self.noteheadFill = general_note.noteheadFill
 150                else:
 151                    self.noteshape = parent_chord.notehead
 152                    self.noteheadFill = parent_chord.noteheadFill
 153                    self.noteheadParenthesis = parent_chord.noteheadParenthesis
 154
 155        # compute the representation of NoteNode as in the paper
 156        # pitches is a list  of elements, each one is (pitchposition, accidental, tied)
 157        self.pitches: list[tuple[str, str, bool]]
 158        if isinstance(general_note, m21.chord.ChordBase):
 159            notes: tuple[m21.note.NotRest, ...] = general_note.notes
 160            if hasattr(general_note, "sortDiatonicAscending"):
 161                # PercussionChords don't have this
 162                notes = general_note.sortDiatonicAscending().notes
 163            self.pitches = []
 164            for p in notes:
 165                if not isinstance(p, (m21.note.Note, m21.note.Unpitched)):
 166                    raise TypeError("The chord must contain only Note or Unpitched")
 167                self.pitches.append(M21Utils.note2tuple(p, detail))
 168
 169        elif isinstance(general_note, (m21.note.Note, m21.note.Unpitched, m21.note.Rest)):
 170            self.pitches = [M21Utils.note2tuple(general_note, detail)]
 171        else:
 172            raise TypeError("The generalNote must be a Chord, a Rest, a Note, or an Unpitched")
 173
 174        dur: m21.duration.Duration = carrier.duration
 175        # note head
 176        type_number = Fraction(
 177            M21Utils.get_type_num(dur)
 178        )
 179        self.note_head: int | Fraction
 180        if type_number >= 4:
 181            self.note_head = 4
 182        else:
 183            self.note_head = type_number
 184        # dots
 185        self.dots: int = dur.dots
 186        # graceness
 187        self.graceType: str = ''
 188        self.graceSlash: bool | None = False
 189        if isinstance(dur, m21.duration.AppoggiaturaDuration):
 190            self.graceType = 'acc'
 191            self.graceSlash = dur.slash
 192        elif isinstance(dur, m21.duration.GraceDuration):
 193            # might be accented or unaccented.  duration.slash isn't always reliable
 194            # (historically), but we can use it as a fallback.
 195            # Check duration.stealTimePrevious and duration.stealTimeFollowing first.
 196            if dur.stealTimePrevious is not None:
 197                self.graceType = 'unacc'
 198            elif dur.stealTimeFollowing is not None:
 199                self.graceType = 'acc'
 200            elif dur.slash is True:
 201                self.graceType = 'unacc'
 202            elif dur.slash is False:
 203                self.graceType = 'acc'
 204            else:
 205                # by default, GraceDuration with no other indications (slash is None)
 206                # is assumed to be unaccented.
 207                self.graceType = 'unacc'
 208            self.graceSlash = dur.slash
 209
 210        # The following (articulations, expressions) only occur once per chord
 211        # or standalone note, so we only want to annotate them once.  We annotate them
 212        # on standalone notes (of course), and on the first note of a parent_chord.
 213        self.articulations: list[str] = []
 214        self.expressions: list[str] = []
 215
 216        if self.note_idx_in_chord is None or self.note_idx_in_chord == 0:
 217            # articulations
 218            if DetailLevel.includesArticulations(detail):
 219                self.articulations = [
 220                    M21Utils.articulation_to_string(a, detail) for a in carrier.articulations
 221                ]
 222                if self.articulations:
 223                    self.articulations.sort()
 224
 225            if DetailLevel.includesOrnaments(detail):
 226                # expressions (tremolo, arpeggio, textexp have their own detail bits, though)
 227                for a in carrier.expressions:
 228                    if not DetailLevel.includesTremolos(detail):
 229                        if isinstance(a, m21.expressions.Tremolo):
 230                            continue
 231                    if not DetailLevel.includesArpeggios(detail):
 232                        if isinstance(a, m21.expressions.ArpeggioMark):
 233                            continue
 234                    if not DetailLevel.includesDirections(detail):
 235                        if isinstance(a, m21.expressions.TextExpression):
 236                            continue
 237                    self.expressions.append(
 238                        M21Utils.expression_to_string(a, detail)
 239                    )
 240                if self.expressions:
 241                    self.expressions.sort()
 242
 243        # precomputed representations for faster comparison
 244        self.precomputed_str: str = self.__str__()
 245
 246    def notation_size(self) -> int:
 247        """
 248        Compute a measure of how many symbols are displayed in the score for this `AnnNote`.
 249
 250        Returns:
 251            int: The notation size of the annotated note
 252        """
 253        size: int = 0
 254        # add for the pitches
 255        for pitch in self.pitches:
 256            size += M21Utils.pitch_size(pitch)
 257        # add for the dots
 258        size += self.dots * len(self.pitches)  # one dot for each note if it's a chord
 259        # add for the beamings
 260        size += len(self.beamings)
 261        # add for the tuplets
 262        size += len(self.tuplets)
 263        # add for the articulations
 264        size += len(self.articulations)
 265        # add for the expressions
 266        size += len(self.expressions)
 267        return size
 268
 269    def get_identifying_string(self, name: str = "") -> str:
 270        string: str = ""
 271        if self.fullNameSuffix.endswith("rest"):
 272            string = self.fullNameSuffix
 273        elif self.fullNameSuffix.endswith("note"):
 274            string = self.pitches[0][0]
 275            if self.pitches[0][1] != "None":
 276                string += " " + self.pitches[0][1]
 277            string += " (" + self.fullNameSuffix + ")"
 278        elif self.fullNameSuffix.endswith("chord"):
 279            string = "["
 280            for p in self.pitches:  # add for pitches
 281                string += p[0]  # pitch name and octave
 282                if p[1] != "None":
 283                    string += " " + p[1]  # pitch accidental
 284                string += ","
 285            string = string[:-1]  # delete the last comma
 286            string += "] (" + self.fullNameSuffix + ")"
 287        return string
 288
 289    def readable_str(self, name: str = "", idx: int = 0, changedStr: str = "") -> str:
 290        string: str = self.get_identifying_string(name)
 291        if name == "pitch":
 292            # this is only for "pitch", not for "" (pitches are in identifying string)
 293            if self.fullNameSuffix.endswith("chord"):
 294                string += f", pitch[{idx}]={self.pitches[idx][0]}"
 295            return string
 296
 297        if name == "accid":
 298            # this is only for "accid" (indexed in a chord), not for "", or for "accid" on a note
 299            # (accidental is in identifying string)
 300            if self.fullNameSuffix.endswith("chord"):
 301                string += f", accid[{idx}]={self.pitches[idx][1]}"
 302            return string
 303
 304        if name == "head":
 305            # this is only for "head", not for "" (head is implied by identifying string)
 306            if self.note_head == 4:
 307                string += ", head=normal"
 308            else:
 309                string += f", head={m21.duration.typeFromNumDict[float(self.note_head)]}"
 310            if name:
 311                return string
 312
 313        if name == "dots":
 314            # this is only for "dots", not for "" (dots is in identifying string)
 315            string += f", dots={self.dots}"
 316            return string
 317
 318        if not name or name == "flagsbeams":
 319            numBeams: int = len(self.beamings)
 320            # Flags are implied by identifying string, so do not belong when name=="".
 321            # And "no beams" is boring for name=="".  Non-zero beams, though, we always
 322            # want to see.
 323            if numBeams == 0:
 324                if name:
 325                    string += ", no flags/beams"
 326                    return string
 327            elif all(b == "partial" for b in self.beamings):
 328                if name:
 329                    if numBeams == 1:
 330                        string += f", {numBeams} flag"
 331                    else:
 332                        string += f", {numBeams} flags"
 333                    return string
 334            else:
 335                # it's beams, not flags
 336                if numBeams == 1:
 337                    string += f", {numBeams} beam="
 338                else:
 339                    string += f", {numBeams} beams=["
 340                for i, b in enumerate(self.beamings):
 341                    if i > 0:
 342                        string += ", "
 343                    string += b
 344                if numBeams > 1:
 345                    string += "]"
 346                if name:
 347                    return string
 348
 349        if not name or name == "tuplet":
 350            if name or self.tuplets:
 351                string += ", tuplets=["
 352                for i, (tup, ti) in enumerate(zip(self.tuplets, self.tuplet_info)):
 353                    if i > 0:
 354                        string += ", "
 355                    if ti != "":
 356                        ti = "(" + ti + ")"
 357                    string += tup + ti
 358
 359                string += "]"
 360                if name:
 361                    return string
 362
 363        if not name or name == "tie":
 364            if self.pitches[idx][2]:
 365                string += ", tied"
 366            elif name:
 367                string += ", not tied"
 368            if name:
 369                return string
 370
 371
 372        if not name or name == "grace":
 373            if not name:
 374                if self.graceType:
 375                    string += f", grace={self.graceType}"
 376            else:
 377                string += f", grace={self.graceType}"
 378            if name:
 379                return string
 380
 381        if not name or name == "graceslash":
 382            if self.graceType:
 383                if self.graceSlash:
 384                    string += ", with grace slash"
 385                else:
 386                    string += ", with no grace slash"
 387            if name:
 388                return string
 389
 390        if not name or name == "noteshape":
 391            if not name:
 392                if self.noteshape != "normal":
 393                    string += f", noteshape={self.noteshape}"
 394            else:
 395                string += f", noteshape={self.noteshape}"
 396            if name:
 397                return string
 398
 399        if not name or name == "notefill":
 400            if not name:
 401                if self.noteheadFill is not None:
 402                    string += f", noteheadFill={self.noteheadFill}"
 403            else:
 404                string += f", noteheadFill={self.noteheadFill}"
 405            if name:
 406                return string
 407
 408        if not name or name == "noteparen":
 409            if not name:
 410                if self.noteheadParenthesis:
 411                    string += f", noteheadParenthesis={self.noteheadParenthesis}"
 412            else:
 413                string += f", noteheadParenthesis={self.noteheadParenthesis}"
 414            if name:
 415                return string
 416
 417        if not name or name == "stemdir":
 418            if not name:
 419                if self.stemDirection != "unspecified":
 420                    string += f", stemDirection={self.stemDirection}"
 421            else:
 422                string += f", stemDirection={self.stemDirection}"
 423            if name:
 424                return string
 425
 426        if not name or name == "spacebefore":
 427            if not name:
 428                if self.gap_dur != 0:
 429                    string += f", spacebefore={self.gap_dur}"
 430            else:
 431                string += f", spacebefore={self.gap_dur}"
 432            if name:
 433                return string
 434
 435        if not name or name == "artic":
 436            if name or self.articulations:
 437                string += ", articulations=["
 438                for i, artic in enumerate(self.articulations):
 439                    if i > 0:
 440                        string += ", "
 441                    string += artic
 442                string += "]"
 443            if name:
 444                return string
 445
 446        if not name or name == "expression":
 447            if name or self.expressions:
 448                string += ", expressions=["
 449                for i, exp in enumerate(self.expressions):
 450                    if i > 0:
 451                        string += ", "
 452                    string += exp
 453                string += "]"
 454            if name:
 455                return string
 456
 457        if not name or name == "style":
 458            if name or self.styledict:
 459                allOfThem: bool = False
 460                changedKeys: list[str] = []
 461                if changedStr:
 462                    changedKeys = changedStr.split(",")
 463                else:
 464                    changedKeys = [str(k) for k in self.styledict]
 465                    allOfThem = True
 466
 467                if allOfThem:
 468                    string += ", style={"
 469                else:
 470                    string += ", changedStyle={"
 471
 472                needsComma: bool = False
 473                for i, k in enumerate(changedKeys):
 474                    if k in self.styledict:
 475                        if needsComma:
 476                            string += ", "
 477                        string += f"{k}:{self.styledict[k]}"
 478                        needsComma = True
 479                string += "}"
 480            if name:
 481                return string
 482
 483        return string
 484
 485    def __repr__(self) -> str:
 486        # must include a unique id for memoization!
 487        # we use the music21 id of the general note.
 488        return (
 489            f"GeneralNote({self.general_note}),G:{self.gap_dur},"
 490            + f"P:{self.pitches},H:{self.note_head},D:{self.dots},"
 491            + f"B:{self.beamings},T:{self.tuplets},TI:{self.tuplet_info},"
 492            + f"A:{self.articulations},E:{self.expressions},"
 493            + f"S:{self.styledict}"
 494        )
 495
 496    def __str__(self) -> str:
 497        """
 498        Returns:
 499            str: the representation of the Annotated note. Does not consider MEI id
 500        """
 501        string: str = "["
 502        for p in self.pitches:  # add for pitches
 503            string += p[0]
 504            if p[1] != "None":
 505                string += p[1]
 506            if p[2]:
 507                string += "T"
 508            string += ","
 509        string = string[:-1]  # delete the last comma
 510        string += "]"
 511        string += str(self.note_head)  # add for notehead
 512        for _ in range(self.dots):  # add for dots
 513            string += "*"
 514        if self.graceType:
 515            string += self.graceType
 516            if self.graceSlash:
 517                string += "/"
 518        if len(self.beamings) > 0:  # add for beaming
 519            string += "B"
 520            for b in self.beamings:
 521                if b == "start":
 522                    string += "sr"
 523                elif b == "continue":
 524                    string += "co"
 525                elif b == "stop":
 526                    string += "sp"
 527                elif b == "partial":
 528                    string += "pa"
 529                else:
 530                    raise ValueError(f"Incorrect beaming type: {b}")
 531
 532        if len(self.tuplets) > 0:  # add for tuplets
 533            string += "T"
 534            for tup, ti in zip(self.tuplets, self.tuplet_info):
 535                if ti != "":
 536                    ti = "(" + ti + ")"
 537                if tup == "start":
 538                    string += "sr" + ti
 539                elif tup == "continue":
 540                    string += "co" + ti
 541                elif tup == "stop":
 542                    string += "sp" + ti
 543                elif tup == "startStop":
 544                    string += "ss"
 545                else:
 546                    raise ValueError(f"Incorrect tuplet type: {tup}")
 547
 548        if len(self.articulations) > 0:  # add for articulations
 549            for a in self.articulations:
 550                string += " " + a
 551        if len(self.expressions) > 0:  # add for expressions
 552            for e in self.expressions:
 553                string += " " + e
 554
 555        if self.noteshape != "normal":
 556            string += f" noteshape={self.noteshape}"
 557        if self.noteheadFill is not None:
 558            string += f" noteheadFill={self.noteheadFill}"
 559        if self.noteheadParenthesis:
 560            string += f" noteheadParenthesis={self.noteheadParenthesis}"
 561        if self.stemDirection != "unspecified":
 562            string += f" stemDirection={self.stemDirection}"
 563
 564        # gap_dur
 565        if self.gap_dur != 0:
 566            string += f" spaceBefore={self.gap_dur}"
 567
 568        # and then the style fields
 569        for i, (k, v) in enumerate(self.styledict.items()):
 570            if i == 0:
 571                string += " "
 572            if i > 0:
 573                string += ","
 574            string += f"{k}={v}"
 575
 576        return string
 577
 578    def get_note_ids(self) -> list[str | int]:
 579        """
 580        Computes a list of the GeneralNote ids for this `AnnNote`.  Since there
 581        is only one GeneralNote here, this will always be a single-element list.
 582
 583        Returns:
 584            [int]: A list containing the single GeneralNote id for this note.
 585        """
 586        return [self.general_note]
 587
 588    def __eq__(self, other) -> bool:
 589        # equality does not consider the MEI id!
 590        return self.precomputed_str == other.precomputed_str
 591
 592
 593class AnnExtra:
 594    def __init__(
 595        self,
 596        extra: m21.base.Music21Object,
 597        measure: m21.stream.Measure,
 598        score: m21.stream.Score,
 599        detail: DetailLevel | int = DetailLevel.Default
 600    ) -> None:
 601        """
 602        Extend music21 non-GeneralNote and non-Stream objects with some precomputed,
 603        easily compared information about it.
 604
 605        Examples: TextExpression, Dynamic, Clef, Key, TimeSignature, MetronomeMark, etc.
 606
 607        Args:
 608            extra (music21.base.Music21Object): The music21 non-GeneralNote/non-Stream
 609                object to extend.
 610            measure (music21.stream.Measure): The music21 Measure the extra was found in.
 611                If the extra was found in a Voice, this is the Measure that the Voice was
 612                found in.
 613            detail (DetailLevel | int): What level of detail to use during the diff.
 614                Can be DecoratedNotesAndRests, OtherObjects, AllObjects, Default (currently
 615                AllObjects), or any combination (with | or &~) of those or NotesAndRests,
 616                Beams, Tremolos, Ornaments, Articulations, Ties, Slurs, Signatures,
 617                Directions, Barlines, StaffDetails, ChordSymbols, Ottavas, Arpeggios, Lyrics,
 618                Style, Metadata, or Voicing.
 619        """
 620        self.extra = extra.id
 621        self.offset: OffsetQL
 622        self.duration: OffsetQL
 623        self.numNotes: int = 1
 624
 625        if isinstance(extra, m21.spanner.Spanner):
 626            self.numNotes = len(extra)
 627            firstNote: m21.note.GeneralNote | m21.spanner.SpannerAnchor = (
 628                M21Utils.getPrimarySpannerElement(extra)
 629            )
 630            lastNote: m21.note.GeneralNote | m21.spanner.SpannerAnchor = (
 631                extra.getLast()
 632            )
 633            self.offset = firstNote.getOffsetInHierarchy(measure)
 634            # to compute duration we need to use offset-in-score, since the end note might
 635            # be in another Measure.  Except for ArpeggioMarkSpanners, where the duration
 636            # doesn't matter, so we just set it to 0, rather than figuring out the longest
 637            # duration in all the notes/chords in the arpeggio.
 638            if isinstance(extra, m21.expressions.ArpeggioMarkSpanner):
 639                self.duration = 0.
 640            else:
 641                startOffsetInScore: OffsetQL = firstNote.getOffsetInHierarchy(score)
 642                try:
 643                    endOffsetInScore: OffsetQL = opFrac(
 644                        lastNote.getOffsetInHierarchy(score) + lastNote.duration.quarterLength
 645                    )
 646                except m21.sites.SitesException:
 647                    endOffsetInScore = startOffsetInScore
 648                self.duration = opFrac(endOffsetInScore - startOffsetInScore)
 649        elif isinstance(extra, m21.bar.Barline):
 650            # we ignore offset for barlines; barline offset is derived from the objects in the
 651            # measure, which are already being compared.
 652            self.offset = 0.0
 653            self.duration = extra.duration.quarterLength
 654        elif isinstance(extra, m21.harmony.ChordSymbol):
 655            # we ignore duration for ChordSymbols, it is often 0.0 or 1.0, and meaningless.
 656            self.offset = extra.getOffsetInHierarchy(measure)
 657            self.duration = 0.0
 658        else:
 659            self.offset = extra.getOffsetInHierarchy(measure)
 660            self.duration = extra.duration.quarterLength
 661
 662        self.content: str = M21Utils.extra_to_string(extra, detail)
 663        self.styledict: dict = {}
 664
 665        if DetailLevel.includesStyle(detail):
 666            if not isinstance(extra, m21.harmony.ChordSymbol):
 667                # We don't (yet) compare style of ChordSymbols, because Humdrum has no way (yet)
 668                # of storing that.
 669                if M21Utils.has_style(extra):
 670                    # includes extra.placement if present
 671
 672                    # special case: MM with text='SMUFLNote = nnn" is being annotated as if there is
 673                    # no text, so none of the text style stuff should be added.
 674                    smuflTextSuppressed: bool = False
 675                    if (isinstance(extra, m21.tempo.MetronomeMark)
 676                            and not extra.textImplicit
 677                            and extra.text
 678                            and not self.content.startswith('MM:TX:')):
 679                        smuflTextSuppressed = True
 680
 681                    self.styledict = M21Utils.obj_to_styledict(
 682                        extra,
 683                        detail,
 684                        smuflTextSuppressed=smuflTextSuppressed
 685                    )
 686
 687        # so far, always 1, but maybe some extra will be bigger someday
 688        self._notation_size: int = 1
 689
 690        # precomputed representations for faster comparison
 691        self.precomputed_str: str = self.__str__()
 692
 693    def notation_size(self) -> int:
 694        """
 695        Compute a measure of how many symbols are displayed in the score for this `AnnExtra`.
 696
 697        Returns:
 698            int: The notation size of the annotated extra
 699        """
 700        return self._notation_size
 701
 702    def readable_str(self, name: str = "", idx: int = 0, changedStr: str = "") -> str:
 703        string: str = self.content
 704        if name == "":
 705            if self.duration > 0:
 706                string += f" dur={M21Utils.ql_to_string(self.duration)}"
 707            if self.numNotes != 1:
 708                string += f" numNotes={self.numNotes}"
 709            return string
 710
 711        if name == "content":
 712            return string
 713
 714        if name == "offset":
 715            string += f" offset={M21Utils.ql_to_string(self.offset)}"
 716            return string
 717
 718        if name == "duration":
 719            string += f" dur={M21Utils.ql_to_string(self.duration)}"
 720            return string
 721
 722        if name == "style":
 723            changedKeys: list[str] = changedStr.split(',')
 724            if not changedKeys:
 725                string += " changedStyle={}"
 726                return string
 727
 728            string += " changedStyle={"
 729
 730            needsComma: bool = False
 731            for i, k in enumerate(changedKeys):
 732                if k in self.styledict:
 733                    if needsComma:
 734                        string += ", "
 735                    string += f"{k}:{self.styledict[k]}"
 736                    needsComma = True
 737            string += "}"
 738            return string
 739
 740        return ""  # should never get here
 741
 742    def __repr__(self) -> str:
 743        # must include a unique id for memoization!
 744        # we use the music21 id of the extra.
 745        output: str = f"Extra({self.extra}):"
 746        output += str(self)
 747        return output
 748
 749    def __str__(self) -> str:
 750        """
 751        Returns:
 752            str: the compared representation of the AnnExtra. Does not consider music21 id.
 753        """
 754        string = f'{self.content},off={self.offset},dur={self.duration}'
 755        if self.numNotes != 1:
 756            string += f',numNotes={self.numNotes}'
 757        # and then any style fields
 758        for k, v in self.styledict.items():
 759            string += f",{k}={v}"
 760        return string
 761
 762    def __eq__(self, other) -> bool:
 763        # equality does not consider the MEI id!
 764        return self.precomputed_str == other.precomputed_str
 765

 767class AnnLyric:
 768    def __init__(
 769        self,
 770        lyric_holder: m21.note.GeneralNote,  # note containing the lyric
 771        lyric: m21.note.Lyric,  # the lyric itself
 772        measure: m21.stream.Measure,
 773        detail: DetailLevel | int = DetailLevel.Default
 774    ) -> None:
 775        """
 776        Extend a lyric from a music21 GeneralNote with some precomputed, easily
 777        compared information about it.
 778
 779        Args:
 780            lyric_holder (music21.note.GeneralNote): The note/chord/rest containing the lyric.
 781            lyric (music21.note.Lyric): The music21 Lyric object to extend.
 782            measure (music21.stream.Measure): The music21 Measure the lyric was found in.
 783                If the lyric was found in a Voice, this is the Measure that the lyric was
 784                found in.
 785            detail (DetailLevel | int): What level of detail to use during the diff.
 786                Can be DecoratedNotesAndRests, OtherObjects, AllObjects, Default (currently
 787                AllObjects), or any combination (with | or &~) of those or NotesAndRests,
 788                Beams, Tremolos, Ornaments, Articulations, Ties, Slurs, Signatures,
 789                Directions, Barlines, StaffDetails, ChordSymbols, Ottavas, Arpeggios, Lyrics,
 790                Style, Metadata, or Voicing.
 791        """
 792        self.lyric_holder = lyric_holder.id
 793
 794        # for comparison: lyric, number, identifier, offset, styledict
 795        self.lyric: str = ""
 796        self.number: int = 0
 797        self.identifier: str = ""
 798        self.offset = lyric_holder.getOffsetInHierarchy(measure)
 799        self.styledict: dict[str, str] = {}
 800
 801        # ignore .syllabic and .text, what is visible is .rawText (and there
 802        # are several .syllabic/.text combos that create the same .rawText).
 803        self.lyric = lyric.rawText
 804
 805        if lyric.number is not None:
 806            self.number = lyric.number
 807
 808        if (lyric._identifier is not None
 809                and lyric._identifier != lyric.number
 810                and lyric._identifier != str(lyric.number)):
 811            self.identifier = lyric._identifier
 812
 813        if DetailLevel.includesStyle(detail) and M21Utils.has_style(lyric):
 814            self.styledict = M21Utils.obj_to_styledict(lyric, detail)
 815            if self.styledict:
 816                # sort styleDict before converting to string so we can compare strings
 817                self.styledict = dict(sorted(self.styledict.items()))
 818
 819        self._notation_size: int = 1
 820
 821        # precomputed representations for faster comparison
 822        self.precomputed_str: str = self.__str__()
 823
 824    def notation_size(self) -> int:
 825        """
 826        Compute a measure of how many symbols are displayed in the score for this `AnnLyric`.
 827
 828        Returns:
 829            int: The notation size of the annotated extra
 830        """
 831        return self._notation_size
 832
 833    def readable_str(self, name: str = "", idx: int = 0, changedStr: str = "") -> str:
 834        string: str = f'"{self.lyric}"'
 835        if name == "":
 836            if self.number is not None:
 837                string += f", num={self.number}"
 838            if self.identifier:  # not None and != ""
 839                string += f", id={self.identifier}"
 840            if self.styledict:
 841                string += f" style={self.styledict}"
 842            return string
 843
 844        if name == "rawtext":
 845            return string
 846
 847        if name == "offset":
 848            string += f" offset={M21Utils.ql_to_string(self.offset)}"
 849            return string
 850
 851        if name == "num":
 852            string += f", num={self.number}"
 853            return string
 854
 855        if name == "id":
 856            string += f", id={self.identifier}"
 857            return string
 858
 859        if name == "style":
 860            string += f" style={self.styledict}"
 861            return string
 862
 863        return ""  # should never get here
 864
 865    def __repr__(self) -> str:
 866        # must include a unique id for memoization!
 867        # we use the music21 id of the general note
 868        # that holds the lyric, plus the lyric
 869        # number within that general note.
 870        output: str = f"Lyric({self.lyric_holder}[{self.number}]):"
 871        output += str(self)
 872        return output
 873
 874    def __str__(self) -> str:
 875        """
 876        Returns:
 877            str: the compared representation of the AnnLyric. Does not consider music21 id.
 878        """
 879        string = (
 880            f"{self.lyric},num={self.number},id={self.identifier}"
 881            + f",off={self.offset},style={self.styledict}"
 882        )
 883        return string
 884
 885    def __eq__(self, other) -> bool:
 886        # equality does not consider the MEI id!
 887        return self.precomputed_str == other.precomputed_str

 890class AnnVoice:
 891    def __init__(
 892        self,
 893        voice: m21.stream.Voice | m21.stream.Measure,
 894        enclosingMeasure: m21.stream.Measure,
 895        detail: DetailLevel | int = DetailLevel.Default
 896    ) -> None:
 897        """
 898        Extend music21 Voice with some precomputed, easily compared information about it.
 899        Only ever called if detail includes Voicing.
 900
 901        Args:
 902            voice (music21.stream.Voice or Measure): The music21 voice to extend. This
 903                can be a Measure, but only if it contains no Voices.
 904            detail (DetailLevel | int): What level of detail to use during the diff.
 905                Can be DecoratedNotesAndRests, OtherObjects, AllObjects, Default (currently
 906                AllObjects), or any combination (with | or &~) of those or NotesAndRests,
 907                Beams, Tremolos, Ornaments, Articulations, Ties, Slurs, Signatures,
 908                Directions, Barlines, StaffDetails, ChordSymbols, Ottavas, Arpeggios, Lyrics,
 909                Style, Metadata, or Voicing.
 910        """
 911        self.voice: int | str = voice.id
 912        note_list: list[m21.note.GeneralNote] = []
 913
 914        if DetailLevel.includesNotesAndRests(detail):
 915            note_list = M21Utils.get_notes_and_gracenotes(voice)
 916
 917        self.en_beam_list: list[list[str]] = []
 918        self.tuplet_list: list[list[str]] = []
 919        self.tuplet_info: list[list[str]] = []
 920        self.annot_notes: list[AnnNote] = []
 921
 922        if note_list:
 923            self.en_beam_list = M21Utils.get_enhance_beamings(
 924                note_list,
 925                detail
 926            )  # beams ("partial" can mean partial beam or just a flag)
 927            self.tuplet_list = M21Utils.get_tuplets_type(
 928                note_list
 929            )  # corrected tuplets (with "start" and "continue")
 930            self.tuplet_info = M21Utils.get_tuplets_info(note_list)
 931            # create a list of notes with beaming and tuplets information attached
 932            self.annot_notes = []
 933            for i, n in enumerate(note_list):
 934                expectedOffsetInMeas: OffsetQL = 0
 935                if i > 0:
 936                    prevNoteStart: OffsetQL = (
 937                        note_list[i - 1].getOffsetInHierarchy(enclosingMeasure)
 938                    )
 939                    prevNoteDurQL: OffsetQL = (
 940                        note_list[i - 1].duration.quarterLength
 941                    )
 942                    expectedOffsetInMeas = opFrac(prevNoteStart + prevNoteDurQL)
 943
 944                gapDurQL: OffsetQL = (
 945                    n.getOffsetInHierarchy(enclosingMeasure) - expectedOffsetInMeas
 946                )
 947                self.annot_notes.append(
 948                    AnnNote(
 949                        n,
 950                        gapDurQL,
 951                        self.en_beam_list[i],
 952                        self.tuplet_list[i],
 953                        self.tuplet_info[i],
 954                        detail=detail
 955                    )
 956                )
 957
 958        self.n_of_notes: int = len(self.annot_notes)
 959        self.precomputed_str: str = self.__str__()
 960
 961    def __eq__(self, other) -> bool:
 962        # equality does not consider MEI id!
 963        if not isinstance(other, AnnVoice):
 964            return False
 965
 966        if len(self.annot_notes) != len(other.annot_notes):
 967            return False
 968
 969        return self.precomputed_str == other.precomputed_str
 970
 971    def notation_size(self) -> int:
 972        """
 973        Compute a measure of how many symbols are displayed in the score for this `AnnVoice`.
 974
 975        Returns:
 976            int: The notation size of the annotated voice
 977        """
 978        return sum([an.notation_size() for an in self.annot_notes])
 979
 980    def readable_str(self, name: str = "", idx: int = 0, changedStr: str = "") -> str:
 981        string: str = "["
 982        for an in self.annot_notes:
 983            string += an.readable_str()
 984            string += ","
 985
 986        if string[-1] == ",":
 987            # delete the last comma
 988            string = string[:-1]
 989
 990        string += "]"
 991        return string
 992
 993    def __repr__(self) -> str:
 994        # must include a unique id for memoization!
 995        # we use the music21 id of the voice.
 996        string: str = f"Voice({self.voice}):"
 997        string += "["
 998        for an in self.annot_notes:
 999            string += repr(an)
1000            string += ","
1001
1002        if string[-1] == ",":
1003            # delete the last comma
1004            string = string[:-1]
1005
1006        string += "]"
1007        return string
1008
1009    def __str__(self) -> str:
1010        string = "["
1011        for an in self.annot_notes:
1012            string += str(an)
1013            string += ","
1014
1015        if string[-1] == ",":
1016            # delete the last comma
1017            string = string[:-1]
1018
1019        string += "]"
1020        return string
1021
1022    def get_note_ids(self) -> list[str | int]:
1023        """
1024        Computes a list of the GeneralNote ids for this `AnnVoice`.
1025
1026        Returns:
1027            [int]: A list containing the GeneralNote ids contained in this voice
1028        """
1029        return [an.general_note for an in self.annot_notes]

1032class AnnMeasure:
1033    def __init__(
1034        self,
1035        measure: m21.stream.Measure,
1036        part: m21.stream.Part,
1037        score: m21.stream.Score,
1038        spannerBundle: m21.spanner.SpannerBundle,
1039        detail: DetailLevel | int = DetailLevel.Default
1040    ) -> None:
1041        """
1042        Extend music21 Measure with some precomputed, easily compared information about it.
1043
1044        Args:
1045            measure (music21.stream.Measure): The music21 Measure to extend.
1046            part (music21.stream.Part): the enclosing music21 Part
1047            score (music21.stream.Score): the enclosing music21 Score.
1048            spannerBundle (music21.spanner.SpannerBundle): a bundle of all the spanners
1049                in the score.
1050            detail (DetailLevel | int): What level of detail to use during the diff.
1051                Can be DecoratedNotesAndRests, OtherObjects, AllObjects, Default (currently
1052                AllObjects), or any combination (with | or &~) of those or NotesAndRests,
1053                Beams, Tremolos, Ornaments, Articulations, Ties, Slurs, Signatures,
1054                Directions, Barlines, StaffDetails, ChordSymbols, Ottavas, Arpeggios, Lyrics,
1055                Style, Metadata, or Voicing.
1056        """
1057        self.measure: int | str = measure.id
1058        self.includes_voicing: bool = DetailLevel.includesVoicing(detail)
1059        self.n_of_elements: int = 0
1060
1061        # for text output only (see self.readable_str())
1062        self.measureNumber: str = M21Utils.get_measure_number_with_suffix(measure, part)
1063        # if self.measureNumber == 135:
1064        #     print('135')
1065
1066        if self.includes_voicing:
1067            # we make an AnnVoice for each voice in the measure
1068            self.voices_list: list[AnnVoice] = []
1069            if len(measure.voices) == 0:
1070                # there is a single AnnVoice (i.e. in the music21 Measure there are no voices)
1071                ann_voice = AnnVoice(measure, measure, detail)
1072                if ann_voice.n_of_notes > 0:
1073                    self.voices_list.append(ann_voice)
1074            else:  # there are multiple voices (or an array with just one voice)
1075                for voice in measure.voices:
1076                    ann_voice = AnnVoice(voice, measure, detail)
1077                    if ann_voice.n_of_notes > 0:
1078                        self.voices_list.append(ann_voice)
1079            self.n_of_elements = len(self.voices_list)
1080        else:
1081            # we pull up all the notes in all the voices (and split any chords into
1082            # individual notes)
1083            self.annot_notes: list[AnnNote] = []
1084
1085            note_list: list[m21.note.GeneralNote] = []
1086            if DetailLevel.includesNotesAndRests(detail):
1087                note_list = M21Utils.get_notes_and_gracenotes(measure, recurse=True)
1088
1089            if note_list:
1090                en_beam_list = M21Utils.get_enhance_beamings(
1091                    note_list,
1092                    detail
1093                )  # beams ("partial" can mean partial beam or just a flag)
1094                tuplet_list = M21Utils.get_tuplets_type(
1095                    note_list
1096                )  # corrected tuplets (with "start" and "continue")
1097                tuplet_info = M21Utils.get_tuplets_info(note_list)
1098
1099                # create a list of notes with beaming and tuplets information attached
1100                self.annot_notes = []
1101                for i, n in enumerate(note_list):
1102                    if isinstance(n, m21.chord.ChordBase):
1103                        if isinstance(n, m21.chord.Chord):
1104                            n.sortDiatonicAscending(inPlace=True)
1105                        chord_offset: OffsetQL = n.getOffsetInHierarchy(measure)
1106                        for n1 in n.notes:
1107                            self.annot_notes.append(
1108                                AnnNote(
1109                                    n1,
1110                                    0.,
1111                                    en_beam_list[i],
1112                                    tuplet_list[i],
1113                                    tuplet_info[i],
1114                                    parent_chord=n,
1115                                    chord_offset=chord_offset,
1116                                    detail=detail
1117                                )
1118                            )
1119                    else:
1120                        self.annot_notes.append(
1121                            AnnNote(
1122                                n,
1123                                0.,
1124                                en_beam_list[i],
1125                                tuplet_list[i],
1126                                tuplet_info[i],
1127                                detail=detail
1128                            )
1129                        )
1130
1131            self.n_of_elements = len(self.annot_notes)
1132
1133        self.extras_list: list[AnnExtra] = []
1134        for extra in M21Utils.get_extras(measure, part, score, spannerBundle, detail):
1135            self.extras_list.append(AnnExtra(extra, measure, score, detail))
1136        self.n_of_elements += len(self.extras_list)
1137
1138        # For correct comparison, sort the extras_list, so that any extras
1139        # that all have the same offset are sorted alphabetically.
1140        self.extras_list.sort(key=lambda e: (e.offset, str(e)))
1141
1142        self.lyrics_list: list[AnnLyric] = []
1143        if DetailLevel.includesLyrics(detail):
1144            for lyric_holder in M21Utils.get_lyrics_holders(measure):
1145                for lyric in lyric_holder.lyrics:
1146                    if lyric.rawText:
1147                        # we ignore lyrics with no visible text
1148                        self.lyrics_list.append(AnnLyric(lyric_holder, lyric, measure, detail))
1149            self.n_of_elements += len(self.lyrics_list)
1150
1151            # For correct comparison, sort the lyrics_list, so that any lyrics
1152            # that all have the same offset are sorted by verse number.
1153            if self.lyrics_list:
1154                self.lyrics_list.sort(key=lambda lyr: (lyr.offset, lyr.number))
1155
1156        # precomputed values to speed up the computation. As they start to be long, they are hashed
1157        self.precomputed_str: int = hash(self.__str__())
1158        self.precomputed_repr: int = hash(self.__repr__())
1159
1160    def __str__(self) -> str:
1161        output: str = ''
1162        if self.includes_voicing:
1163            output += str([str(v) for v in self.voices_list])
1164        else:
1165            output += str([str(n) for n in self.annot_notes])
1166        if self.extras_list:
1167            output += ' Extras:' + str([str(e) for e in self.extras_list])
1168        if self.lyrics_list:
1169            output += ' Lyrics:' + str([str(lyr) for lyr in self.lyrics_list])
1170        return output
1171
1172    def __repr__(self) -> str:
1173        # must include a unique id for memoization!
1174        # we use the music21 id of the measure.
1175        output: str = f"Measure({self.measure}):"
1176        if self.includes_voicing:
1177            output += str([repr(v) for v in self.voices_list])
1178        else:
1179            output += str([repr(n) for n in self.annot_notes])
1180        if self.extras_list:
1181            output += ' Extras:' + str([repr(e) for e in self.extras_list])
1182        if self.lyrics_list:
1183            output += ' Lyrics:' + str([repr(lyr) for lyr in self.lyrics_list])
1184        return output
1185
1186    def __eq__(self, other) -> bool:
1187        # equality does not consider MEI id!
1188        if not isinstance(other, AnnMeasure):
1189            return False
1190
1191        if self.includes_voicing and other.includes_voicing:
1192            if len(self.voices_list) != len(other.voices_list):
1193                return False
1194        elif not self.includes_voicing and not other.includes_voicing:
1195            if len(self.annot_notes) != len(other.annot_notes):
1196                return False
1197        else:
1198            # shouldn't ever happen, but I guess it could if the client does weird stuff
1199            return False
1200
1201        if len(self.extras_list) != len(other.extras_list):
1202            return False
1203
1204        if len(self.lyrics_list) != len(other.lyrics_list):
1205            return False
1206
1207        return self.precomputed_str == other.precomputed_str
1208        # return all([v[0] == v[1] for v in zip(self.voices_list, other.voices_list)])

1210    def readable_str(self, name: str = "", idx: int = 0, changedStr: str = "") -> str:
1211        string: str = f"measure {self.measureNumber}"
1212        return string

1214    def notation_size(self) -> int:
1215        """
1216        Compute a measure of how many symbols are displayed in the score for this `AnnMeasure`.
1217
1218        Returns:
1219            int: The notation size of the annotated measure
1220        """
1221        if self.includes_voicing:
1222            return (
1223                sum([v.notation_size() for v in self.voices_list])
1224                + sum([e.notation_size() for e in self.extras_list])
1225            )
1226
1227        return (
1228            sum([n.notation_size() for n in self.annot_notes])
1229            + sum([e.notation_size() for e in self.extras_list])
1230        )
1231
1232
1233    def get_note_ids(self) -> list[str | int]:
1234        """
1235        Computes a list of the GeneralNote ids for this `AnnMeasure`.
1236
1237        Returns:
1238            [int]: A list containing the GeneralNote ids contained in this measure
1239        """
1240        notes_id = []
1241        if self.includes_voicing:
1242            for v in self.voices_list:
1243                notes_id.extend(v.get_note_ids())
1244        else:
1245            for n in self.annot_notes:
1246                notes_id.extend(n.get_note_ids())
1247        return notes_id

1250class AnnPart:
1251    def __init__(
1252        self,
1253        part: m21.stream.Part,
1254        score: m21.stream.Score,
1255        spannerBundle: m21.spanner.SpannerBundle,
1256        detail: DetailLevel | int = DetailLevel.Default
1257    ):
1258        """
1259        Extend music21 Part/PartStaff with some precomputed, easily compared information about it.
1260
1261        Args:
1262            part (music21.stream.Part, music21.stream.PartStaff): The music21 Part/PartStaff
1263                to extend.
1264            score (music21.stream.Score): the enclosing music21 Score.
1265            spannerBundle (music21.spanner.SpannerBundle): a bundle of all the spanners in
1266                the score.
1267            detail (DetailLevel | int): What level of detail to use during the diff.
1268                Can be DecoratedNotesAndRests, OtherObjects, AllObjects, Default (currently
1269                AllObjects), or any combination (with | or &~) of those or NotesAndRests,
1270                Beams, Tremolos, Ornaments, Articulations, Ties, Slurs, Signatures,
1271                Directions, Barlines, StaffDetails, ChordSymbols, Ottavas, Arpeggios, Lyrics,
1272                Style, Metadata, or Voicing.
1273        """
1274        self.part: int | str = part.id
1275        self.bar_list: list[AnnMeasure] = []
1276        for measure in part.getElementsByClass("Measure"):
1277            # create the bar objects
1278            ann_bar = AnnMeasure(measure, part, score, spannerBundle, detail)
1279            if ann_bar.n_of_elements > 0:
1280                self.bar_list.append(ann_bar)
1281        self.n_of_bars: int = len(self.bar_list)
1282        # Precomputed str to speed up the computation.
1283        # String itself is pretty long, so it is hashed
1284        self.precomputed_str: int = hash(self.__str__())
1285
1286    def __str__(self) -> str:
1287        output: str = 'Part: '
1288        output += str([str(b) for b in self.bar_list])
1289        return output
1290
1291    def __eq__(self, other) -> bool:
1292        # equality does not consider MEI id!
1293        if not isinstance(other, AnnPart):
1294            return False
1295
1296        if len(self.bar_list) != len(other.bar_list):
1297            return False
1298
1299        return all(b[0] == b[1] for b in zip(self.bar_list, other.bar_list))
1300
1301    def notation_size(self) -> int:
1302        """
1303        Compute a measure of how many symbols are displayed in the score for this `AnnPart`.
1304
1305        Returns:
1306            int: The notation size of the annotated part
1307        """
1308        return sum([b.notation_size() for b in self.bar_list])
1309
1310    def __repr__(self) -> str:
1311        # must include a unique id for memoization!
1312        # we use the music21 id of the part.
1313        output: str = f"Part({self.part}):"
1314        output += str([repr(b) for b in self.bar_list])
1315        return output

1318        """
1319        Computes a list of the GeneralNote ids for this `AnnPart`.
1320
1321        Returns:
1322            [int]: A list containing the GeneralNote ids contained in this part
1323        """
1324        notes_id = []

1330class AnnStaffGroup:
1331    def __init__(
1332        self,
1333        staff_group: m21.layout.StaffGroup,
1334        part_to_index: dict[m21.stream.Part, int],
1335        detail: DetailLevel | int = DetailLevel.Default
1336    ) -> None:
1337        """
1338        Take a StaffGroup and store it as an annotated object.
1339        """
1340        self.staff_group: int | str = staff_group.id
1341        self.name: str = staff_group.name or ''
1342        self.abbreviation: str = staff_group.abbreviation or ''
1343        self.symbol: str | None = None
1344        self.barTogether: bool | str | None = staff_group.barTogether
1345
1346        if DetailLevel.includesStyle(detail):
1347            # symbol (brace, bracket, line, etc) is considered to be style
1348            self.symbol = staff_group.symbol
1349
1350        self.part_indices: list[int] = []
1351        for part in staff_group:
1352            self.part_indices.append(part_to_index.get(part, -1))
1353
1354        # sort so simple list comparison can work
1355        self.part_indices.sort()
1356
1357        self.n_of_parts: int = len(self.part_indices)
1358
1359        # precomputed representations for faster comparison
1360        self.precomputed_str: str = self.__str__()
1361
1362    def __str__(self) -> str:
1363        output: str = "StaffGroup"
1364        if self.name and self.abbreviation:
1365            output += f"({self.name},{self.abbreviation})"
1366        elif self.name:
1367            output += f"({self.name})"
1368        elif self.abbreviation:
1369            output += f"(,{self.abbreviation})"
1370        else:
1371            output += "(,)"
1372
1373        output += f", partIndices={self.part_indices}"
1374        if self.symbol is not None:
1375            output += f", symbol={self.symbol}"
1376        if self.barTogether is not None:
1377            output += f", barTogether={self.barTogether}"
1378        return output
1379
1380    def __eq__(self, other) -> bool:
1381        # equality does not consider MEI id (or MEI ids of parts included in the group)
1382        if not isinstance(other, AnnStaffGroup):
1383            return False
1384
1385        if self.name != other.name:
1386            return False
1387
1388        if self.abbreviation != other.abbreviation:
1389            return False
1390
1391        if self.symbol != other.symbol:
1392            return False
1393
1394        if self.barTogether != other.barTogether:
1395            return False
1396
1397        if self.part_indices != other.part_indices:
1398            return False
1399
1400        return True
1401
1402    def readable_str(self, name: str = "", idx: int = 0, changedStr: str = "") -> str:
1403        string: str = f"StaffGroup{self.part_indices}"
1404        if name == "":
1405            return string
1406
1407        if name == "name":
1408            string += f" name={self.name}"
1409            return string
1410
1411        if name == "abbr":
1412            string += f" abbr={self.abbreviation}"
1413            return string
1414
1415        if name == "sym":
1416            string += f" sym={self.symbol}"
1417            return string
1418
1419        if name == "barline":
1420            string += f" barTogether={self.barTogether}"
1421            return string
1422
1423        if name == "parts":
1424            # main string already has parts in it
1425            return string
1426
1427        return ""

1430        """
1431        Compute a measure of how many symbols are displayed in the score for this `AnnStaffGroup`.
1432
1433        Returns:
1434            int: The notation size of the annotated staff group
1435        """
1436        # notation_size = 5 because there are 5 main visible things about a StaffGroup:
1437        #   name, abbreviation, symbol shape, barline type, and which parts it encloses
1438        return 5

1450class AnnMetadataItem:
1451    def __init__(
1452        self,
1453        key: str,
1454        value: t.Any
1455    ) -> None:
1456        # Normally this would be the id of the Music21Object, but we just have a key/value
1457        # pair, so we just make up an id, by using our own address.  In this case, we will
1458        # not be looking this id up in the score, but only using it as a memo-ization key.
1459        self.metadata_item = id(self)
1460        self.key = key
1461        if isinstance(value, m21.metadata.Text):
1462            # Create a string representing both the text and the language, but not isTranslated,
1463            # since isTranslated cannot be represented in many file formats.
1464            self.value = (
1465                self.make_value_string(value)
1466                + f'(language={value.language})'
1467            )
1468        elif isinstance(value, m21.metadata.Contributor):
1469            # Create a string (same thing: value.name.isTranslated will differ randomly)
1470            # Currently I am also ignoring more than one name, and birth/death.
1471            if not value._names:
1472                # ignore this metadata item
1473                self.key = ''
1474                self.value = ''
1475                return
1476
1477            self.value = self.make_value_string(value)
1478            roleEmitted: bool = False
1479            if value.role:
1480                if value.role == 'poet':
1481                    # special case: many MusicXML files have the lyricist listed as the poet.
1482                    # We compare them as equivalent here.
1483                    lyr: str = 'lyricist'
1484                    self.key = lyr
1485                    self.value += f'(role={lyr}'
1486                else:
1487                    self.value += f'(role={value.role}'
1488                roleEmitted = True
1489            if value._names:
1490                if roleEmitted:
1491                    self.value += ', '
1492                self.value += f'language={value._names[0].language}'
1493            if roleEmitted:
1494                self.value += ')'
1495        else:
1496            self.value = value
1497
1498    def __eq__(self, other) -> bool:
1499        if not isinstance(other, AnnMetadataItem):
1500            return False
1501
1502        if self.key != other.key:
1503            return False
1504
1505        if self.value != other.value:
1506            return False
1507
1508        return True
1509
1510    def readable_str(self, name: str = "", idx: int = 0, changedStr: str = "") -> str:
1511        return str(self)
1512
1513    def __str__(self) -> str:
1514        return self.key + ':' + str(self.value)
1515
1516
1517    def __repr__(self) -> str:
1518        # must include a unique id for memoization!
1519        # We use id(self), because there is no music21 object here.
1520        output: str = f"MetadataItem({self.metadata_item}):"
1521        output += self.key + ':' + str(self.value)
1522        return output
1523
1524    def notation_size(self) -> int:
1525        """
1526        Compute a measure of how many symbols are displayed in the score for this `AnnMetadataItem`.
1527
1528        Returns:
1529            int: The notation size of the annotated metadata item
1530        """
1531        return 1
1532
1533    def make_value_string(self, value: m21.metadata.Contributor | m21.metadata.Text) -> str:
1534        # Unescapes a bunch of stuff (and strips off leading/trailing whitespace)
1535        output: str = str(value)
1536        output = output.strip()
1537        output = html.unescape(output)
1538        return output
