1541class AnnScore:
1542    def __init__(
1543        self,
1544        score: m21.stream.Score,
1545        detail: DetailLevel | int = DetailLevel.Default
1546    ) -> None:
1547        """
1548        Take a music21 score and store it as a sequence of Full Trees.
1549        The hierarchy is "score -> parts -> measures -> voices -> notes"
1550        Args:
1551            score (music21.stream.Score): The music21 score
1552            detail (DetailLevel | int): What level of detail to use during the diff.
1553                Can be DecoratedNotesAndRests, OtherObjects, AllObjects, Default (currently
1554                AllObjects), or any combination (with | or &~) of those or NotesAndRests,
1555                Beams, Tremolos, Ornaments, Articulations, Ties, Slurs, Signatures,
1556                Directions, Barlines, StaffDetails, ChordSymbols, Ottavas, Arpeggios, Lyrics,
1557                Style, Metadata, or Voicing.
1558        """
1559        self.score: int | str = score.id
1560        self.part_list: list[AnnPart] = []
1561        self.staff_group_list: list[AnnStaffGroup] = []
1562        self.metadata_items_list: list[AnnMetadataItem] = []
1563
1564        spannerBundle: m21.spanner.SpannerBundle = score.spannerBundle
1565        part_to_index: dict[m21.stream.Part, int] = {}
1566
1567        # Before we start, transpose all notes to written pitch, both for transposing
1568        # instruments and Ottavas. Be careful to preserve accidental.displayStatus
1569        # during transposition, since we use that visibility indicator when comparing
1570        # accidentals.
1571        score.toWrittenPitch(inPlace=True, preserveAccidentalDisplay=True)
1572
1573        for idx, part in enumerate(score.parts):
1574            # create and add the AnnPart object to part_list
1575            # and to part_to_index dict
1576            part_to_index[part] = idx
1577            ann_part = AnnPart(part, score, spannerBundle, detail)
1578            self.part_list.append(ann_part)
1579
1580        self.n_of_parts: int = len(self.part_list)
1581
1582        if DetailLevel.includesStaffDetails(detail):
1583            for staffGroup in score[m21.layout.StaffGroup]:
1584                # ignore any StaffGroup that contains all the parts, and has no symbol
1585                # and has no barthru (this is just a placeholder generated by some
1586                # file formats, and has the same meaning if it is missing).
1587                if len(staffGroup) == len(part_to_index):
1588                    if not staffGroup.symbol and not staffGroup.barTogether:
1589                        continue
1590
1591                ann_staff_group = AnnStaffGroup(staffGroup, part_to_index, detail)
1592                if ann_staff_group.n_of_parts > 0:
1593                    self.staff_group_list.append(ann_staff_group)
1594
1595        if DetailLevel.includesMetadata(detail) and score.metadata:
1596            # m21 metadata.all() can't sort primitives, so we'll have to sort by hand.
1597            # Note: we sort metadata_items_list after the fact, because sometimes
1598            # (e.g. otherContributor:poet) we substitute names (e.g. lyricist:)
1599            allItems: list[tuple[str, t.Any]] = list(
1600                score.metadata.all(returnPrimitives=True, returnSorted=False)
1601            )
1602            for key, value in allItems:
1603                if key in ('fileFormat', 'filePath', 'software'):
1604                    # Don't compare metadata items that are uninterestingly different.
1605                    continue
1606                if (key.startswith('raw:')
1607                        or key.startswith('meiraw:')
1608                        or key.startswith('humdrumraw:')):
1609                    # Don't compare verbatim/raw metadata ('meiraw:meihead',
1610                    # 'raw:freeform', 'humdrumraw:XXX'), it's often deleted
1611                    # when made obsolete by conversions/edits.
1612                    continue
1613                if key in ('humdrum:EMD', 'humdrum:EST', 'humdrum:VTS',
1614                        'humdrum:RLN', 'humdrum:PUB'):
1615                    # Don't compare metadata items that should never be transferred
1616                    # from one file to another.  'humdrum:EMD' is a modification
1617                    # description entry, humdrum:EST is "current encoding status"
1618                    # (i.e. complete or some value of not complete), 'humdrum:VTS'
1619                    # is a checksum of the Humdrum file, 'humdrum:RLN' is the
1620                    # extended ASCII encoding of the Humdrum file, 'humdrum:PUB'
1621                    # is the publication status of the file (published or not?).
1622                    continue
1623                ami: AnnMetadataItem = AnnMetadataItem(key, value)
1624                if ami.key and ami.value:
1625                    self.metadata_items_list.append(ami)
1626
1627            self.metadata_items_list.sort(key=lambda each: (each.key, str(each.value)))
1628
1629    def __eq__(self, other) -> bool:
1630        # equality does not consider MEI id!
1631        if not isinstance(other, AnnScore):
1632            return False
1633
1634        if len(self.part_list) != len(other.part_list):
1635            return False
1636
1637        return all(p[0] == p[1] for p in zip(self.part_list, other.part_list))
1638
1639    def notation_size(self) -> int:
1640        """
1641        Compute a measure of how many symbols are displayed in the score for this `AnnScore`.
1642
1643        Returns:
1644            int: The notation size of the annotated score
1645        """
1646        return sum([p.notation_size() for p in self.part_list])
1647
1648    def __repr__(self) -> str:
1649        # must include a unique id for memoization!
1650        # we use the music21 id of the score.
1651        output: str = f"Score({self.score}):"
1652        output += str(repr(p) for p in self.part_list)
1653        return output
1654
1655    def get_note_ids(self) -> list[str | int]:
1656        """
1657        Computes a list of the GeneralNote ids for this `AnnScore`.
1658
1659        Returns:
1660            [int]: A list containing the GeneralNote ids contained in this score
1661        """
1662        notes_id = []
1663        for p in self.part_list:
1664            notes_id.extend(p.get_note_ids())
1665        return notes_id
1666
1667    # return the sequences of measures for a specified part
1668    def _measures_from_part(self, part_number) -> list[AnnMeasure]:
1669        # only used by tests/test_scl.py
1670        if part_number not in range(0, len(self.part_list)):
1671            raise ValueError(
1672                f"parameter 'part_number' should be between 0 and {len(self.part_list) - 1}"
1673            )
1674        return self.part_list[part_number].bar_list
class AnnNote: 
 28class AnnNote:
 29    def __init__(
 30        self,
 31        general_note: m21.note.GeneralNote,
 32        gap_dur: OffsetQL,
 33        enhanced_beam_list: list[str],
 34        tuplet_list: list[str],
 35        tuplet_info: list[str],
 36        parent_chord: m21.chord.ChordBase | None = None,
 37        chord_offset: OffsetQL | None = None,  # only set if this note is inside a chord
 38        detail: DetailLevel | int = DetailLevel.Default,
 39    ) -> None:
 40        """
 41        Extend music21 GeneralNote with some precomputed, easily compared information about it.
 42
 43        Args:
 44            general_note (music21.note.GeneralNote): The music21 note/chord/rest to extend.
 45            gap_dur (OffsetQL): gap since end of last note (or since start of measure, if
 46                first note in measure).  Usually zero.
 47            enhanced_beam_list (list): A list of beaming information about this GeneralNote.
 48            tuplet_list (list): A list of basic tuplet info about this GeneralNote.
 49            tuplet_info (list): A list of detailed tuplet info about this GeneralNote.
 50            detail (DetailLevel | int): What level of detail to use during the diff.
 51                Can be DecoratedNotesAndRests, OtherObjects, AllObjects, Default (currently
 52                AllObjects), or any combination (with | or &~) of those or NotesAndRests,
 53                Beams, Tremolos, Ornaments, Articulations, Ties, Slurs, Signatures,
 54                Directions, Barlines, StaffDetails, ChordSymbols, Ottavas, Arpeggios, Lyrics,
 55                Style, Metadata, or Voicing.
 56        """
 57        self.general_note: int | str = general_note.id
 58        self.is_in_chord: bool = False
 59        self.note_idx_in_chord: int | None = None
 60        if parent_chord is not None:
 61            # This is what visualization uses to color the note red (chord id and note idx)
 62            self.general_note = parent_chord.id
 63            self.is_in_chord = True
 64            self.note_idx_in_chord = parent_chord.notes.index(general_note)
 65
 66        # A lot of stuff is carried by the parent_chord (if present) or the
 67        # general_note (if parent_chord not present); we call that the carrier
 68        carrier: m21.note.GeneralNote = parent_chord or general_note
 69
 70        self.gap_dur: OffsetQL = gap_dur
 71        self.beamings: list[str] = enhanced_beam_list
 72        self.tuplets: list[str] = tuplet_list
 73        self.tuplet_info: list[str] = tuplet_info
 74
 75        self.note_offset: OffsetQL = 0.
 76        self.note_dur_type: str = ''
 77        self.note_dur_dots: int = 0
 78        self.note_is_grace: bool = False
 79
 80        # fullNameSuffix is only for text output, it is not involved in comparison at all.
 81        # It is of the form "Dotted Quarter Rest", etc.
 82        self.fullNameSuffix: str = general_note.duration.fullName
 83        if isinstance(general_note, m21.note.Rest):
 84            self.fullNameSuffix += " Rest"
 85        elif isinstance(general_note, m21.chord.ChordBase):
 86            if parent_chord is None:
 87                self.fullNameSuffix += " Chord"
 88            else:
 89                # we're actually annotating one of the notes in the chord
 90                self.fullNameSuffix += " Note"
 91        elif isinstance(general_note, (m21.note.Note, m21.note.Unpitched)):
 92            self.fullNameSuffix += " Note"
 93        else:
 94            self.fullNameSuffix += " Note"
 95        self.fullNameSuffix = self.fullNameSuffix.lower()
 96
 97        if not DetailLevel.includesVoicing(detail):
 98            # if we're comparing the individual notes, we need to make a note of
 99            # offset and visual duration to be used later when searching for matching
100            # notes in the measures being compared.
101
102            # offset
103            if chord_offset is None:
104                self.note_offset = general_note.offset
105            else:
106                self.note_offset = chord_offset
107
108            # visual duration and graceness
109            self.note_dur_type = carrier.duration.type
110            self.note_dur_dots = carrier.duration.dots
111            self.note_is_grace = carrier.duration.isGrace
112
113        self.styledict: dict = {}
114
115        if DetailLevel.includesStyle(detail):
116            # we will take style from the individual note, and then override with
117            # style from the chord (following music21's MusicXML exporter).
118            if M21Utils.has_style(general_note):
119                self.styledict = M21Utils.obj_to_styledict(general_note, detail)
120
121            if parent_chord is not None:
122                if M21Utils.has_style(parent_chord):
123                    parentstyledict = M21Utils.obj_to_styledict(parent_chord, detail)
124                    for k, v in parentstyledict.items():
125                        self.styledict[k] = v
126
127        self.noteshape: str = 'normal'
128        self.noteheadFill: bool | None = None
129        self.noteheadParenthesis: bool = False
130        self.stemDirection: str = 'unspecified'
131        if DetailLevel.includesStyle(detail) and isinstance(general_note, m21.note.NotRest):
132            if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
133                # because general_note is NotRest, parent_chord must also be (might be
134                # a chord instead of a note, but that still works)
135                assert isinstance(carrier, m21.note.NotRest)
136            self.stemDirection = carrier.stemDirection
137
138            if parent_chord is None:
139                self.noteshape = general_note.notehead
140                self.noteheadFill = general_note.noteheadFill
141                self.noteheadParenthesis = general_note.noteheadParenthesis
142            else:
143                # try general_note first, but if nothing about note head is specified,
144                # go with whatever parent_chord says.
145                if (general_note.notehead != 'normal'
146                        or general_note.noteheadParenthesis
147                        or general_note.noteheadFill is not None):
148                    self.noteheadParenthesis = general_note.noteheadParenthesis
149                    self.noteshape = general_note.notehead
150                    self.noteheadFill = general_note.noteheadFill
151                else:
152                    self.noteshape = parent_chord.notehead
153                    self.noteheadFill = parent_chord.noteheadFill
154                    self.noteheadParenthesis = parent_chord.noteheadParenthesis
155
156        # compute the representation of NoteNode as in the paper
157        # pitches is a list  of elements, each one is (pitchposition, accidental, tied)
158        self.pitches: list[tuple[str, str, bool]]
159        if isinstance(general_note, m21.chord.ChordBase):
160            notes: tuple[m21.note.NotRest, ...] = general_note.notes
161            if hasattr(general_note, "sortDiatonicAscending"):
162                # PercussionChords don't have this
163                notes = general_note.sortDiatonicAscending().notes
164            self.pitches = []
165            for p in notes:
166                if not isinstance(p, (m21.note.Note, m21.note.Unpitched)):
167                    raise TypeError("The chord must contain only Note or Unpitched")
168                self.pitches.append(M21Utils.note2tuple(p, detail))
169
170        elif isinstance(general_note, (m21.note.Note, m21.note.Unpitched, m21.note.Rest)):
171            self.pitches = [M21Utils.note2tuple(general_note, detail)]
172        else:
173            raise TypeError("The generalNote must be a Chord, a Rest, a Note, or an Unpitched")
174
175        dur: m21.duration.Duration = carrier.duration
176        # note head
177        type_number = Fraction(
178            M21Utils.get_type_num(dur)
179        )
180        self.note_head: int | Fraction
181        if type_number >= 4:
182            self.note_head = 4
183        else:
184            self.note_head = type_number
185        # dots
186        self.dots: int = dur.dots
187        # graceness
188        self.graceType: str = ''
189        self.graceSlash: bool | None = False
190        if isinstance(dur, m21.duration.AppoggiaturaDuration):
191            self.graceType = 'acc'
192            self.graceSlash = dur.slash
193        elif isinstance(dur, m21.duration.GraceDuration):
194            # might be accented or unaccented.  duration.slash isn't always reliable
195            # (historically), but we can use it as a fallback.
196            # Check duration.stealTimePrevious and duration.stealTimeFollowing first.
197            if dur.stealTimePrevious is not None:
198                self.graceType = 'unacc'
199            elif dur.stealTimeFollowing is not None:
200                self.graceType = 'acc'
201            elif dur.slash is True:
202                self.graceType = 'unacc'
203            elif dur.slash is False:
204                self.graceType = 'acc'
205            else:
206                # by default, GraceDuration with no other indications (slash is None)
207                # is assumed to be unaccented.
208                self.graceType = 'unacc'
209            self.graceSlash = dur.slash
210
211        # The following (articulations, expressions) only occur once per chord
212        # or standalone note, so we only want to annotate them once.  We annotate them
213        # on standalone notes (of course), and on the first note of a parent_chord.
214        self.articulations: list[str] = []
215        self.expressions: list[str] = []
216
217        if self.note_idx_in_chord is None or self.note_idx_in_chord == 0:
218            # articulations
219            if DetailLevel.includesArticulations(detail):
220                self.articulations = [
221                    M21Utils.articulation_to_string(a, detail) for a in carrier.articulations
222                ]
223                if self.articulations:
224                    self.articulations.sort()
225
226            if DetailLevel.includesOrnaments(detail):
227                # expressions (tremolo, arpeggio, textexp have their own detail bits, though)
228                for a in carrier.expressions:
229                    if not DetailLevel.includesTremolos(detail):
230                        if isinstance(a, m21.expressions.Tremolo):
231                            continue
232                    if not DetailLevel.includesArpeggios(detail):
233                        if isinstance(a, m21.expressions.ArpeggioMark):
234                            continue
235                    if not DetailLevel.includesDirections(detail):
236                        if isinstance(a, m21.expressions.TextExpression):
237                            continue
238                    self.expressions.append(
239                        M21Utils.expression_to_string(a, detail)
240                    )
241                if self.expressions:
242                    self.expressions.sort()
243
244        # precomputed representations for faster comparison
245        self.precomputed_str: str = self.__str__()
246
247    def notation_size(self) -> int:
248        """
249        Compute a measure of how many symbols are displayed in the score for this `AnnNote`.
250
251        Returns:
252            int: The notation size of the annotated note
253        """
254        size: int = 0
255        # add for the pitches
256        for pitch in self.pitches:
257            size += M21Utils.pitch_size(pitch)
258        # add for the dots
259        size += self.dots * len(self.pitches)  # one dot for each note if it's a chord
260        # add for the beamings
261        size += len(self.beamings)
262        # add for the tuplets
263        size += len(self.tuplets)
264        # add for the articulations
265        size += len(self.articulations)
266        # add for the expressions
267        size += len(self.expressions)
268        return size
269
270    def get_identifying_string(self, name: str = "") -> str:
271        string: str = ""
272        if self.fullNameSuffix.endswith("rest"):
273            string = self.fullNameSuffix
274        elif self.fullNameSuffix.endswith("note"):
275            string = self.pitches[0][0]
276            if self.pitches[0][1] != "None":
277                string += " " + self.pitches[0][1]
278            string += " (" + self.fullNameSuffix + ")"
279        elif self.fullNameSuffix.endswith("chord"):
280            string = "["
281            for p in self.pitches:  # add for pitches
282                string += p[0]  # pitch name and octave
283                if p[1] != "None":
284                    string += " " + p[1]  # pitch accidental
285                string += ","
286            string = string[:-1]  # delete the last comma
287            string += "] (" + self.fullNameSuffix + ")"
288        return string
289
290    def readable_str(self, name: str = "", idx: int = 0, changedStr: str = "") -> str:
291        string: str = self.get_identifying_string(name)
292        if name == "pitch":
293            # this is only for "pitch", not for "" (pitches are in identifying string)
294            if self.fullNameSuffix.endswith("chord"):
295                string += f", pitch[{idx}]={self.pitches[idx][0]}"
296            return string
297
298        if name == "accid":
299            # this is only for "accid" (indexed in a chord), not for "", or for "accid" on a note
300            # (accidental is in identifying string)
301            if self.fullNameSuffix.endswith("chord"):
302                string += f", accid[{idx}]={self.pitches[idx][1]}"
303            return string
304
305        if name == "head":
306            # this is only for "head", not for "" (head is implied by identifying string)
307            if self.note_head == 4:
308                string += ", head=normal"
309            else:
310                string += f", head={m21.duration.typeFromNumDict[float(self.note_head)]}"
311            if name:
312                return string
313
314        if name == "dots":
315            # this is only for "dots", not for "" (dots is in identifying string)
316            string += f", dots={self.dots}"
317            return string
318
319        if not name or name == "flagsbeams":
320            numBeams: int = len(self.beamings)
321            # Flags are implied by identifying string, so do not belong when name=="".
322            # And "no beams" is boring for name=="".  Non-zero beams, though, we always
323            # want to see.
324            if numBeams == 0:
325                if name:
326                    string += ", no flags/beams"
327                    return string
328            elif all(b == "partial" for b in self.beamings):
329                if name:
330                    if numBeams == 1:
331                        string += f", {numBeams} flag"
332                    else:
333                        string += f", {numBeams} flags"
334                    return string
335            else:
336                # it's beams, not flags
337                if numBeams == 1:
338                    string += f", {numBeams} beam="
339                else:
340                    string += f", {numBeams} beams=["
341                for i, b in enumerate(self.beamings):
342                    if i > 0:
343                        string += ", "
344                    string += b
345                if numBeams > 1:
346                    string += "]"
347                if name:
348                    return string
349
350        if not name or name == "tuplet":
351            if name or self.tuplets:
352                string += ", tuplets=["
353                for i, (tup, ti) in enumerate(zip(self.tuplets, self.tuplet_info)):
354                    if i > 0:
355                        string += ", "
356                    if ti != "":
357                        ti = "(" + ti + ")"
358                    string += tup + ti
359
360                string += "]"
361                if name:
362                    return string
363
364        if not name or name == "tie":
365            if self.pitches[idx][2]:
366                string += ", tied"
367            elif name:
368                string += ", not tied"
369            if name:
370                return string
371
372
373        if not name or name == "grace":
374            if not name:
375                if self.graceType:
376                    string += f", grace={self.graceType}"
377            else:
378                string += f", grace={self.graceType}"
379            if name:
380                return string
381
382        if not name or name == "graceslash":
383            if self.graceType:
384                if self.graceSlash:
385                    string += ", with grace slash"
386                else:
387                    string += ", with no grace slash"
388            if name:
389                return string
390
391        if not name or name == "noteshape":
392            if not name:
393                if self.noteshape != "normal":
394                    string += f", noteshape={self.noteshape}"
395            else:
396                string += f", noteshape={self.noteshape}"
397            if name:
398                return string
399
400        if not name or name == "notefill":
401            if not name:
402                if self.noteheadFill is not None:
403                    string += f", noteheadFill={self.noteheadFill}"
404            else:
405                string += f", noteheadFill={self.noteheadFill}"
406            if name:
407                return string
408
409        if not name or name == "noteparen":
410            if not name:
411                if self.noteheadParenthesis:
412                    string += f", noteheadParenthesis={self.noteheadParenthesis}"
413            else:
414                string += f", noteheadParenthesis={self.noteheadParenthesis}"
415            if name:
416                return string
417
418        if not name or name == "stemdir":
419            if not name:
420                if self.stemDirection != "unspecified":
421                    string += f", stemDirection={self.stemDirection}"
422            else:
423                string += f", stemDirection={self.stemDirection}"
424            if name:
425                return string
426
427        if not name or name == "spacebefore":
428            if not name:
429                if self.gap_dur != 0:
430                    string += f", spacebefore={self.gap_dur}"
431            else:
432                string += f", spacebefore={self.gap_dur}"
433            if name:
434                return string
435
436        if not name or name == "artic":
437            if name or self.articulations:
438                string += ", articulations=["
439                for i, artic in enumerate(self.articulations):
440                    if i > 0:
441                        string += ", "
442                    string += artic
443                string += "]"
444            if name:
445                return string
446
447        if not name or name == "expression":
448            if name or self.expressions:
449                string += ", expressions=["
450                for i, exp in enumerate(self.expressions):
451                    if i > 0:
452                        string += ", "
453                    string += exp
454                string += "]"
455            if name:
456                return string
457
458        if not name or name == "style":
459            if name or self.styledict:
460                allOfThem: bool = False
461                changedKeys: list[str] = []
462                if changedStr:
463                    changedKeys = changedStr.split(",")
464                else:
465                    changedKeys = [str(k) for k in self.styledict]
466                    allOfThem = True
467
468                if allOfThem:
469                    string += ", style={"
470                else:
471                    string += ", changedStyle={"
472
473                needsComma: bool = False
474                for i, k in enumerate(changedKeys):
475                    if k in self.styledict:
476                        if needsComma:
477                            string += ", "
478                        string += f"{k}:{self.styledict[k]}"
479                        needsComma = True
480                string += "}"
481            if name:
482                return string
483
484        return string
485
486    def __repr__(self) -> str:
487        # must include a unique id for memoization!
488        # we use the music21 id of the general note.
489        return (
490            f"GeneralNote({self.general_note}),G:{self.gap_dur},"
491            + f"P:{self.pitches},H:{self.note_head},D:{self.dots},"
492            + f"B:{self.beamings},T:{self.tuplets},TI:{self.tuplet_info},"
493            + f"A:{self.articulations},E:{self.expressions},"
494            + f"S:{self.styledict}"
495        )
496
497    def __str__(self) -> str:
498        """
499        Returns:
500            str: the representation of the Annotated note. Does not consider MEI id
501        """
502        string: str = "["
503        for p in self.pitches:  # add for pitches
504            string += p[0]
505            if p[1] != "None":
506                string += p[1]
507            if p[2]:
508                string += "T"
509            string += ","
510        string = string[:-1]  # delete the last comma
511        string += "]"
512        string += str(self.note_head)  # add for notehead
513        for _ in range(self.dots):  # add for dots
514            string += "*"
515        if self.graceType:
516            string += self.graceType
517            if self.graceSlash:
518                string += "/"
519        if len(self.beamings) > 0:  # add for beaming
520            string += "B"
521            for b in self.beamings:
522                if b == "start":
523                    string += "sr"
524                elif b == "continue":
525                    string += "co"
526                elif b == "stop":
527                    string += "sp"
528                elif b == "partial":
529                    string += "pa"
530                else:
531                    raise ValueError(f"Incorrect beaming type: {b}")
532
533        if len(self.tuplets) > 0:  # add for tuplets
534            string += "T"
535            for tup, ti in zip(self.tuplets, self.tuplet_info):
536                if ti != "":
537                    ti = "(" + ti + ")"
538                if tup == "start":
539                    string += "sr" + ti
540                elif tup == "continue":
541                    string += "co" + ti
542                elif tup == "stop":
543                    string += "sp" + ti
544                elif tup == "startStop":
545                    string += "ss"
546                else:
547                    raise ValueError(f"Incorrect tuplet type: {tup}")
548
549        if len(self.articulations) > 0:  # add for articulations
550            for a in self.articulations:
551                string += " " + a
552        if len(self.expressions) > 0:  # add for expressions
553            for e in self.expressions:
554                string += " " + e
555
556        if self.noteshape != "normal":
557            string += f" noteshape={self.noteshape}"
558        if self.noteheadFill is not None:
559            string += f" noteheadFill={self.noteheadFill}"
560        if self.noteheadParenthesis:
561            string += f" noteheadParenthesis={self.noteheadParenthesis}"
562        if self.stemDirection != "unspecified":
563            string += f" stemDirection={self.stemDirection}"
564
565        # gap_dur
566        if self.gap_dur != 0:
567            string += f" spaceBefore={self.gap_dur}"
568
569        # and then the style fields
570        for i, (k, v) in enumerate(self.styledict.items()):
571            if i == 0:
572                string += " "
573            if i > 0:
574                string += ","
575            string += f"{k}={v}"
576
577        return string
578
579    def get_note_ids(self) -> list[str | int]:
580        """
581        Computes a list of the GeneralNote ids for this `AnnNote`.  Since there
582        is only one GeneralNote here, this will always be a single-element list.
583
584        Returns:
585            [int]: A list containing the single GeneralNote id for this note.
586        """
587        return [self.general_note]

589    def __eq__(self, other) -> bool:
590        # equality does not consider the MEI id!
591        return self.precomputed_str == other.precomputed_str
AnnNote( general_note: music21.note.GeneralNote, gap_dur: float | fractions.Fraction, enhanced_beam_list: list[str], tuplet_list: list[str], tuplet_info: list[str], parent_chord: music21.chord.ChordBase | None = None, chord_offset: float | fractions.Fraction | None = None, detail: musicdiff.detaillevel.DetailLevel | int = <DetailLevel.AllObjects: 32767>) 
 29    def __init__(
 30        self,
 31        general_note: m21.note.GeneralNote,
 32        gap_dur: OffsetQL,
 33        enhanced_beam_list: list[str],
 34        tuplet_list: list[str],
 35        tuplet_info: list[str],
 36        parent_chord: m21.chord.ChordBase | None = None,
 37        chord_offset: OffsetQL | None = None,  # only set if this note is inside a chord
 38        detail: DetailLevel | int = DetailLevel.Default,
 39    ) -> None:
 40        """
 41        Extend music21 GeneralNote with some precomputed, easily compared information about it.
 42
 43        Args:
 44            general_note (music21.note.GeneralNote): The music21 note/chord/rest to extend.
 45            gap_dur (OffsetQL): gap since end of last note (or since start of measure, if
 46                first note in measure).  Usually zero.
 47            enhanced_beam_list (list): A list of beaming information about this GeneralNote.
 48            tuplet_list (list): A list of basic tuplet info about this GeneralNote.
 49            tuplet_info (list): A list of detailed tuplet info about this GeneralNote.
 50            detail (DetailLevel | int): What level of detail to use during the diff.
 51                Can be DecoratedNotesAndRests, OtherObjects, AllObjects, Default (currently
 52                AllObjects), or any combination (with | or &~) of those or NotesAndRests,
 53                Beams, Tremolos, Ornaments, Articulations, Ties, Slurs, Signatures,
 54                Directions, Barlines, StaffDetails, ChordSymbols, Ottavas, Arpeggios, Lyrics,
 55                Style, Metadata, or Voicing.
 56        """
 57        self.general_note: int | str = general_note.id
 58        self.is_in_chord: bool = False
 59        self.note_idx_in_chord: int | None = None
 60        if parent_chord is not None:
 61            # This is what visualization uses to color the note red (chord id and note idx)
 62            self.general_note = parent_chord.id
 63            self.is_in_chord = True
 64            self.note_idx_in_chord = parent_chord.notes.index(general_note)
 65
 66        # A lot of stuff is carried by the parent_chord (if present) or the
 67        # general_note (if parent_chord not present); we call that the carrier
 68        carrier: m21.note.GeneralNote = parent_chord or general_note
 69
 70        self.gap_dur: OffsetQL = gap_dur
 71        self.beamings: list[str] = enhanced_beam_list
 72        self.tuplets: list[str] = tuplet_list
 73        self.tuplet_info: list[str] = tuplet_info
 74
 75        self.note_offset: OffsetQL = 0.
 76        self.note_dur_type: str = ''
 77        self.note_dur_dots: int = 0
 78        self.note_is_grace: bool = False
 79
 80        # fullNameSuffix is only for text output, it is not involved in comparison at all.
 81        # It is of the form "Dotted Quarter Rest", etc.
 82        self.fullNameSuffix: str = general_note.duration.fullName
 83        if isinstance(general_note, m21.note.Rest):
 84            self.fullNameSuffix += " Rest"
 85        elif isinstance(general_note, m21.chord.ChordBase):
 86            if parent_chord is None:
 87                self.fullNameSuffix += " Chord"
 88            else:
 89                # we're actually annotating one of the notes in the chord
 90                self.fullNameSuffix += " Note"
 91        elif isinstance(general_note, (m21.note.Note, m21.note.Unpitched)):
 92            self.fullNameSuffix += " Note"
 93        else:
 94            self.fullNameSuffix += " Note"
 95        self.fullNameSuffix = self.fullNameSuffix.lower()
 96
 97        if not DetailLevel.includesVoicing(detail):
 98            # if we're comparing the individual notes, we need to make a note of
 99            # offset and visual duration to be used later when searching for matching
100            # notes in the measures being compared.
101
102            # offset
103            if chord_offset is None:
104                self.note_offset = general_note.offset
105            else:
106                self.note_offset = chord_offset
107
108            # visual duration and graceness
109            self.note_dur_type = carrier.duration.type
110            self.note_dur_dots = carrier.duration.dots
111            self.note_is_grace = carrier.duration.isGrace
112
113        self.styledict: dict = {}
114
115        if DetailLevel.includesStyle(detail):
116            # we will take style from the individual note, and then override with
117            # style from the chord (following music21's MusicXML exporter).
118            if M21Utils.has_style(general_note):
119                self.styledict = M21Utils.obj_to_styledict(general_note, detail)
120
121            if parent_chord is not None:
122                if M21Utils.has_style(parent_chord):
123                    parentstyledict = M21Utils.obj_to_styledict(parent_chord, detail)
124                    for k, v in parentstyledict.items():
125                        self.styledict[k] = v
126
127        self.noteshape: str = 'normal'
128        self.noteheadFill: bool | None = None
129        self.noteheadParenthesis: bool = False
130        self.stemDirection: str = 'unspecified'
131        if DetailLevel.includesStyle(detail) and isinstance(general_note, m21.note.NotRest):
132            if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
133                # because general_note is NotRest, parent_chord must also be (might be
134                # a chord instead of a note, but that still works)
135                assert isinstance(carrier, m21.note.NotRest)
136            self.stemDirection = carrier.stemDirection
137
138            if parent_chord is None:
139                self.noteshape = general_note.notehead
140                self.noteheadFill = general_note.noteheadFill
141                self.noteheadParenthesis = general_note.noteheadParenthesis
142            else:
143                # try general_note first, but if nothing about note head is specified,
144                # go with whatever parent_chord says.
145                if (general_note.notehead != 'normal'
146                        or general_note.noteheadParenthesis
147                        or general_note.noteheadFill is not None):
148                    self.noteheadParenthesis = general_note.noteheadParenthesis
149                    self.noteshape = general_note.notehead
150                    self.noteheadFill = general_note.noteheadFill
151                else:
152                    self.noteshape = parent_chord.notehead
153                    self.noteheadFill = parent_chord.noteheadFill
154                    self.noteheadParenthesis = parent_chord.noteheadParenthesis
155
156        # compute the representation of NoteNode as in the paper
157        # pitches is a list  of elements, each one is (pitchposition, accidental, tied)
158        self.pitches: list[tuple[str, str, bool]]
159        if isinstance(general_note, m21.chord.ChordBase):
160            notes: tuple[m21.note.NotRest, ...] = general_note.notes
161            if hasattr(general_note, "sortDiatonicAscending"):
162                # PercussionChords don't have this
163                notes = general_note.sortDiatonicAscending().notes
164            self.pitches = []
165            for p in notes:
166                if not isinstance(p, (m21.note.Note, m21.note.Unpitched)):
167                    raise TypeError("The chord must contain only Note or Unpitched")
168                self.pitches.append(M21Utils.note2tuple(p, detail))
169
170        elif isinstance(general_note, (m21.note.Note, m21.note.Unpitched, m21.note.Rest)):
171            self.pitches = [M21Utils.note2tuple(general_note, detail)]
172        else:
173            raise TypeError("The generalNote must be a Chord, a Rest, a Note, or an Unpitched")
174
175        dur: m21.duration.Duration = carrier.duration
176        # note head
177        type_number = Fraction(
178            M21Utils.get_type_num(dur)
179        )
180        self.note_head: int | Fraction
181        if type_number >= 4:
182            self.note_head = 4
183        else:
184            self.note_head = type_number
185        # dots
186        self.dots: int = dur.dots
187        # graceness
188        self.graceType: str = ''
189        self.graceSlash: bool | None = False
190        if isinstance(dur, m21.duration.AppoggiaturaDuration):
191            self.graceType = 'acc'
192            self.graceSlash = dur.slash
193        elif isinstance(dur, m21.duration.GraceDuration):
194            # might be accented or unaccented.  duration.slash isn't always reliable
195            # (historically), but we can use it as a fallback.
196            # Check duration.stealTimePrevious and duration.stealTimeFollowing first.
197            if dur.stealTimePrevious is not None:
198                self.graceType = 'unacc'
199            elif dur.stealTimeFollowing is not None:
200                self.graceType = 'acc'
201            elif dur.slash is True:
202                self.graceType = 'unacc'
203            elif dur.slash is False:
204                self.graceType = 'acc'
205            else:
206                # by default, GraceDuration with no other indications (slash is None)
207                # is assumed to be unaccented.
208                self.graceType = 'unacc'
209            self.graceSlash = dur.slash
210
211        # The following (articulations, expressions) only occur once per chord
212        # or standalone note, so we only want to annotate them once.  We annotate them
213        # on standalone notes (of course), and on the first note of a parent_chord.
214        self.articulations: list[str] = []
215        self.expressions: list[str] = []
216
217        if self.note_idx_in_chord is None or self.note_idx_in_chord == 0:
218            # articulations
219            if DetailLevel.includesArticulations(detail):
220                self.articulations = [
221                    M21Utils.articulation_to_string(a, detail) for a in carrier.articulations
222                ]
223                if self.articulations:
224                    self.articulations.sort()
225
226            if DetailLevel.includesOrnaments(detail):
227                # expressions (tremolo, arpeggio, textexp have their own detail bits, though)
228                for a in carrier.expressions:
229                    if not DetailLevel.includesTremolos(detail):
230                        if isinstance(a, m21.expressions.Tremolo):
231                            continue
232                    if not DetailLevel.includesArpeggios(detail):
233                        if isinstance(a, m21.expressions.ArpeggioMark):
234                            continue
235                    if not DetailLevel.includesDirections(detail):
236                        if isinstance(a, m21.expressions.TextExpression):
237                            continue
238                    self.expressions.append(
239                        M21Utils.expression_to_string(a, detail)
240                    )
241                if self.expressions:
242                    self.expressions.sort()
243
244        # precomputed representations for faster comparison
245        self.precomputed_str: str = self.__str__()

def notation_size(self) -> int: 
247    def notation_size(self) -> int:
248        """
249        Compute a measure of how many symbols are displayed in the score for this `AnnNote`.
250
251        Returns:
252            int: The notation size of the annotated note
253        """
254        size: int = 0
255        # add for the pitches
256        for pitch in self.pitches:
257            size += M21Utils.pitch_size(pitch)
258        # add for the dots
259        size += self.dots * len(self.pitches)  # one dot for each note if it's a chord
260        # add for the beamings
261        size += len(self.beamings)
262        # add for the tuplets
263        size += len(self.tuplets)
264        # add for the articulations
265        size += len(self.articulations)
266        # add for the expressions
267        size += len(self.expressions)
268        return size

def get_identifying_string(self, name: str = '') -> str: 
270    def get_identifying_string(self, name: str = "") -> str:
271        string: str = ""
272        if self.fullNameSuffix.endswith("rest"):
273            string = self.fullNameSuffix
274        elif self.fullNameSuffix.endswith("note"):
275            string = self.pitches[0][0]
276            if self.pitches[0][1] != "None":
277                string += " " + self.pitches[0][1]
278            string += " (" + self.fullNameSuffix + ")"
279        elif self.fullNameSuffix.endswith("chord"):
280            string = "["
281            for p in self.pitches:  # add for pitches
282                string += p[0]  # pitch name and octave
283                if p[1] != "None":
284                    string += " " + p[1]  # pitch accidental
285                string += ","
286            string = string[:-1]  # delete the last comma
287            string += "] (" + self.fullNameSuffix + ")"
288        return string

607

610                object to extend.

612                If the extra was found in a Voice, this is the Measure that the Voice was
613                found in.

615                Can be DecoratedNotesAndRests, OtherObjects, AllObjects, Default (currently
616                AllObjects), or any combination (with | or &~) of those or NotesAndRests,
617                Beams, Tremolos, Ornaments, Articulations, Ties, Slurs, Signatures,

622        self.offset: OffsetQL
623        self.duration: OffsetQL
624        self.numNotes: int = 1

627            self.numNotes = len(extra)
628            firstNote: m21.note.GeneralNote | m21.spanner.SpannerAnchor = (
629                M21Utils.getPrimarySpannerElement(extra)

632                extra.getLast()
633            )

635            # to compute duration we need to use offset-in-score, since the end note might
636            # be in another Measure.  Except for ArpeggioMarkSpanners, where the duration
637            # doesn't matter, so we just set it to 0, rather than figuring out the longest
638            # duration in all the notes/chords in the arpeggio.
639            if isinstance(extra, m21.expressions.ArpeggioMarkSpanner):
640                self.duration = 0.

643                try:
644                    endOffsetInScore: OffsetQL = opFrac(
645                        lastNote.getOffsetInHierarchy(score) + lastNote.duration.quarterLength
646                    )
647                except m21.sites.SitesException:
648                    endOffsetInScore = startOffsetInScore
649                self.duration = opFrac(endOffsetInScore - startOffsetInScore)
650        elif isinstance(extra, m21.bar.Barline):
651            # we ignore offset for barlines; barline offset is derived from the objects in the
652            # measure, which are already being compared.
653            self.offset = 0.0
654            self.duration = extra.duration.quarterLength
655        elif isinstance(extra, m21.harmony.ChordSymbol):
656            # we ignore duration for ChordSymbols, it is often 0.0 or 1.0, and meaningless.
657            self.offset = extra.getOffsetInHierarchy(measure)

815            self.styledict = M21Utils.obj_to_styledict(lyric, detail)

 916            note_list = M21Utils.get_notes_and_gracenotes(voice)

 927            )  # beams ("partial" can mean partial beam or just a flag)

 929                note_list

 931            self.tuplet_info = M21Utils.get_tuplets_info(note_list)

 933            self.annot_notes = []

1054                Beams, Tremolos, Ornaments, Articulations, Ties, Slurs, Signatures,
1055                Directions, Barlines, StaffDetails, ChordSymbols, Ottavas, Arpeggios, Lyrics,
1056                Style, Metadata, or Voicing.

1065        #     print('135')

1071                # there is a single AnnVoice (i.e. in the music21 Measure there are no voices)

1073                if ann_voice.n_of_notes > 0:

1111                                    0.,

1117                                    detail=detail
1118                                )
1119                            )
1120                    else:
1121                        self.annot_notes.append(
1122                            AnnNote(
1123                                n,
1124                                0.,
1125                                en_beam_list[i],
1126                                tuplet_list[i],
1127                                tuplet_info[i],
1128                                detail=detail
1129                            )
1130                        )

1136            self.extras_list.append(AnnExtra(extra, measure, score, detail))

1187    def __eq__(self, other) -> bool:
1188        # equality does not consider MEI id!

1190            return False

1192        if self.includes_voicing and other.includes_voicing:

1194                return False
1195        elif not self.includes_voicing and not other.includes_voicing:
1196            if len(self.annot_notes) != len(other.annot_notes):
1197                return False
1198        else:
1199            # shouldn't ever happen, but I guess it could if the client does weird stuff
1200            return False
1201
1202        if len(self.extras_list) != len(other.extras_list):
1203            return False
1204
1205        if len(self.lyrics_list) != len(other.lyrics_list):
1206            return False
1207
1208        return self.precomputed_str == other.precomputed_str

class AnnMetadataItem: 
1451class AnnMetadataItem:
1452    def __init__(
1453        self,
1454        key: str,
1455        value: t.Any
1456    ) -> None:
1457        # Normally this would be the id of the Music21Object, but we just have a key/value
1458        # pair, so we just make up an id, by using our own address.  In this case, we will
1459        # not be looking this id up in the score, but only using it as a memo-ization key.
1460        self.metadata_item = id(self)
1461        self.key = key
1462        if isinstance(value, m21.metadata.Text):
1463            # Create a string representing both the text and the language, but not isTranslated,
1464            # since isTranslated cannot be represented in many file formats.
1465            self.value = (
1466                self.make_value_string(value)
1467                + f'(language={value.language})'
1468            )
1469        elif isinstance(value, m21.metadata.Contributor):
1470            # Create a string (same thing: value.name.isTranslated will differ randomly)
1471            # Currently I am also ignoring more than one name, and birth/death.
1472            if not value._names:
1473                # ignore this metadata item
1474                self.key = ''
1475                self.value = ''
1476                return
1477
1478            self.value = self.make_value_string(value)
1479            roleEmitted: bool = False
1480            if value.role:
1481                if value.role == 'poet':
1482                    # special case: many MusicXML files have the lyricist listed as the poet.
1483                    # We compare them as equivalent here.
1484                    lyr: str = 'lyricist'
1485                    self.key = lyr
1486                    self.value += f'(role={lyr}'
1487                else:
1488                    self.value += f'(role={value.role}'
1489                roleEmitted = True
1490            if value._names:
1491                if roleEmitted:
1492                    self.value += ', '
1493                self.value += f'language={value._names[0].language}'
1494            if roleEmitted:
1495                self.value += ')'
1496        else:
1497            self.value = value
1498

1500        if not isinstance(other, AnnMetadataItem):
1501            return False
1502
1503        if self.key != other.key:
1504            return False
1505
1506        if self.value != other.value:
1507            return False
1508
1509        return True

class AnnScore: 
1542class AnnScore:
1543    def __init__(
1544        self,
1545        score: m21.stream.Score,
1546        detail: DetailLevel | int = DetailLevel.Default
1547    ) -> None:
1548        """
1549        Take a music21 score and store it as a sequence of Full Trees.
1550        The hierarchy is "score -> parts -> measures -> voices -> notes"
1551        Args:
1552            score (music21.stream.Score): The music21 score
1553            detail (DetailLevel | int): What level of detail to use during the diff.
1554                Can be DecoratedNotesAndRests, OtherObjects, AllObjects, Default (currently
1555                AllObjects), or any combination (with | or &~) of those or NotesAndRests,
1556                Beams, Tremolos, Ornaments, Articulations, Ties, Slurs, Signatures,
1557                Directions, Barlines, StaffDetails, ChordSymbols, Ottavas, Arpeggios, Lyrics,
1558                Style, Metadata, or Voicing.
1559        """
1560        self.score: int | str = score.id
1561        self.part_list: list[AnnPart] = []
1562        self.staff_group_list: list[AnnStaffGroup] = []
1563        self.metadata_items_list: list[AnnMetadataItem] = []
1564
1565        spannerBundle: m21.spanner.SpannerBundle = score.spannerBundle
1566        part_to_index: dict[m21.stream.Part, int] = {}
1567
1568        # Before we start, transpose all notes to written pitch, both for transposing
1569        # instruments and Ottavas. Be careful to preserve accidental.displayStatus
1570        # during transposition, since we use that visibility indicator when comparing
1571        # accidentals.
1572        score.toWrittenPitch(inPlace=True, preserveAccidentalDisplay=True)
1573
1574        for idx, part in enumerate(score.parts):
1575            # create and add the AnnPart object to part_list
1576            # and to part_to_index dict
1577            part_to_index[part] = idx
1578            ann_part = AnnPart(part, score, spannerBundle, detail)
1579            self.part_list.append(ann_part)
1580
1581        self.n_of_parts: int = len(self.part_list)
1582
1583        if DetailLevel.includesStaffDetails(detail):
1584            for staffGroup in score[m21.layout.StaffGroup]:
1585                # ignore any StaffGroup that contains all the parts, and has no symbol
1586                # and has no barthru (this is just a placeholder generated by some
1587                # file formats, and has the same meaning if it is missing).
1588                if len(staffGroup) == len(part_to_index):
1589                    if not staffGroup.symbol and not staffGroup.barTogether:
1590                        continue
1591
1592                ann_staff_group = AnnStaffGroup(staffGroup, part_to_index, detail)
1593                if ann_staff_group.n_of_parts > 0:
1594                    self.staff_group_list.append(ann_staff_group)
1595
1596        if DetailLevel.includesMetadata(detail) and score.metadata:
1597            # m21 metadata.all() can't sort primitives, so we'll have to sort by hand.
1598            # Note: we sort metadata_items_list after the fact, because sometimes
1599            # (e.g. otherContributor:poet) we substitute names (e.g. lyricist:)
1600            allItems: list[tuple[str, t.Any]] = list(
1601                score.metadata.all(returnPrimitives=True, returnSorted=False)
1602            )
1603            for key, value in allItems:
1604                if key in ('fileFormat', 'filePath', 'software'):
1605                    # Don't compare metadata items that are uninterestingly different.
1606                    continue
1607                if (key.startswith('raw:')
1608                        or key.startswith('meiraw:')
1609                        or key.startswith('humdrumraw:')):
1610                    # Don't compare verbatim/raw metadata ('meiraw:meihead',
1611                    # 'raw:freeform', 'humdrumraw:XXX'), it's often deleted
1612                    # when made obsolete by conversions/edits.
1613                    continue
1614                if key in ('humdrum:EMD', 'humdrum:EST', 'humdrum:VTS',
1615                        'humdrum:RLN', 'humdrum:PUB'):
1616                    # Don't compare metadata items that should never be transferred
1617                    # from one file to another.  'humdrum:EMD' is a modification
1618                    # description entry, humdrum:EST is "current encoding status"
1619                    # (i.e. complete or some value of not complete), 'humdrum:VTS'
1620                    # is a checksum of the Humdrum file, 'humdrum:RLN' is the
1621                    # extended ASCII encoding of the Humdrum file, 'humdrum:PUB'
1622                    # is the publication status of the file (published or not?).
1623                    continue
1624                ami: AnnMetadataItem = AnnMetadataItem(key, value)
1625                if ami.key and ami.value:
1626                    self.metadata_items_list.append(ami)
1627
1628            self.metadata_items_list.sort(key=lambda each: (each.key, str(each.value)))
1629
1630    def __eq__(self, other) -> bool:
1631        # equality does not consider MEI id!
1632        if not isinstance(other, AnnScore):
1633            return False
1634
1635        if len(self.part_list) != len(other.part_list):
1636            return False
1637
1638        return all(p[0] == p[1] for p in zip(self.part_list, other.part_list))
1639
1640    def notation_size(self) -> int:
1641        """
1642        Compute a measure of how many symbols are displayed in the score for this `AnnScore`.
1643
1644        Returns:
1645            int: The notation size of the annotated score
1646        """
1647        return sum([p.notation_size() for p in self.part_list])
1648
1649    def __repr__(self) -> str:
1650        # must include a unique id for memoization!
1651        # we use the music21 id of the score.
1652        output: str = f"Score({self.score}):"
1653        output += str(repr(p) for p in self.part_list)
1654        return output
1655
1656    def get_note_ids(self) -> list[str | int]:
1657        """
1658        Computes a list of the GeneralNote ids for this `AnnScore`.
1659
1660        Returns:
1661            [int]: A list containing the GeneralNote ids contained in this score
1662        """
1663        notes_id = []
1664        for p in self.part_list:
1665            notes_id.extend(p.get_note_ids())
1666        return notes_id
1667
1668    # return the sequences of measures for a specified part
1669    def _measures_from_part(self, part_number) -> list[AnnMeasure]:
1670        # only used by tests/test_scl.py
1671        if part_number not in range(0, len(self.part_list)):
1672            raise ValueError(
1673                f"parameter 'part_number' should be between 0 and {len(self.part_list) - 1}"
1674            )
1675        return self.part_list[part_number].bar_list
